reviews.text: We are from the state of oregon, sorry about that, but anyways, the service here was wonderful with very friendly staff, prices are reasonable, and and their homemade ice cream was great, I tried the salty malty and it was very good, especially with a fresh waffle cone.

Drove up to Chat Town from Atl on a nice Saturday. My sons and I had a great time walking the area and decided on Clumpies for a sweet treat. Great location and good selection. I'm dairy-free and love sorbet, so their 5 different sorbet flavors work perfect for me. My sons both had a cookie dough milkshake, and 9 had a black cherry freeze. My only knock...the line was out the door, and they were way understaffed for a Saturday. It was just 2 employees working the counter. Really only 1 because the other had to keep the area stocked. Could have definitely used another pair of hands helping out. Other than that, we were totally satisfied customers. As long as you have patients, I would highly recommend stopping in.
The ice cream was very delicious.

Best ice cream In town.
I’ve order led the berry cheesecake and the pumpkin caramel cake. Hubby got cookies and cream and butter pecan👌

Ava, Gabi and Drew were absolutely wonderful. My son has an almond allergy and they were sure to double check ingredients and do a clean scoop in a brand new container of the ice cream for him. Wonderful experience. The ice cream is delicious and the kindness from the team was exemplary! Would love to revisit!

Got 3 of the prepackaged ice cream sandwiches. The person that rang me up (nothing more) scoffed at me for not leaving a tip. She literally scanned three items and was visibly and audibly upset that there wasn't a tip left.

Top that off with the disgusting "cookie" parts of the ice cream sandwich, and we will not be back. Ice cream was mediocre at best-tasted like Breyers.
Ava crushed it with exceptional customer service!!! The ice cream was delish!
We love Clumpies!
The ice cream is ordinary!  Nothing special at all, I can get better at Baskin Robins and better pricing too, just saying.  Guess you could say, been there won’t be back.

I went in today and had such amazing service from Maggie! I ordered the farmhouse biscuit and wasn't a fan of the tomato jam, but Maggie's happy attitude and attentive service really balanced out the visit for me.
We had such a wonderful Valentines Brunch!!! Ro was our server and he made us feel so special. Very knowledgable about the menu, and such a sweet guy!!! 10/10 would recommend!
Matty was a fabulous server, definitely made our experience amazing. The food was also beautiful and delicious the biscuits hit. And the juice was so yummy we got me feel good

Last time I ordered here coffee was fantastic I could not wait to come back and have another one though today was a completely different experience not the same at all guess it goes to show you not everyone is trained the same way

My husband and I dined here for the first time tonight and it was a fabulous experience.  Our host, Alan, was very helpful explaining the specials and delivered wonderful service. The filet and lobster tail was delicious and cooked perfectly.
Alan in the bar excels at customer service. And what a mixologist!  Our first visit, but not our last. Food great. Can't wait to return.

Nice atmosphere and good service. Was very disappointed in the tomahawk steak as it had a large amount of fat and was quite tough. Definitely the worst steak I've ever had at an upscale restaurant. Prices were also quite high considering the serving size.
One of my favorite places to eat. The calzones are amazing 👏

We were looking for a buffet and found this place and I have to say that the food was delicious. They don’t have as much variety as some other places, but the taste makes up for the lack of choices. I had their fried chicken, salad and several vegetables. I also had the banana pudding for dessert. The atmosphere is like a cafeteria and not elegant by far but again, very good food. Our waitress was attentive and checked on us several times to make sure we had refills on our drinks, and anything else we needed. Please check them out. We certainly will go back.

I called and specifically asked if the buffet was $10.99 on the weekends like it is during the week days and I was told it was. I felt like I was intentionally misled.The bill came up to almost $30.00 for two people before tip. Plus they charge a fee for using a card. When I asked why I was told that the cashier goes the weekend dinner price is the same as the week day dinner price which makes no sense because it was like 12pm.  No dessert really. Pizza wasnt out and no cranberry sauce. And its always a debate if the cornbread is available. Probably won't be back.  I wouldn't have came for that price. Might as well went on to another buffet.

Update: There was no menus on the table when my party came in and why would I be looking for signs or a menu when I called ahead of time before I drove across town to restaurant. And I came for the buffet. It's a small restaurant so there's no reason why anyone answering the phone wouldn't know the current price of the meal. Especially a cashier. She literally paused and thought about what she was saying. Could've made sure if she didn't know. I'm sure most people are paying cash. There was nothing on the bar that you don't see during the week. And if you add pizza ever 7 to 8 minutes why was the bar completely out of every kind of pizza. You shouldn't wait till it's completely out to put some out. And I'm confused at dinner time vs lunch time because you don't open till 11 most days and I was there early. No was it was dinner time.
The food was good the waiters were nice and they had a lot of tables

My husband absolutely loves this place. He always gets the buffet and I will order off the menu. I’ve enjoyed everything I’ve ordered but the calzone is probably my favorite dinner item. Breakfast is really good too.

My boyfriend and I stopped in here for brunch on a Sunday around noon. As we expected, they were a little busy but nothing too crazy, the wait was only 20 minutes. However, once we were seated, it took fifteen minutes before we were able to order drinks and the latte I ordered didn’t make it to the table for 40 MINUTES! Once we were finally able to order food, it took over an hour between being seated and getting our meals. We were so perplexed as it looked to us like there was more than enough staff to accommodate the number of guests, but even the tables beside us were complaining about the wait times. The French toast I ordered didn’t not come with the warm spiced peaches as it’s supposed to since they had run out earlier in the day, which is fine, but then why did I still spend $14 on plain french toast? We also ordered a side of bacon that was the driest, most dehydrated bacon we’d ever seen. Just thoroughly disappointed as I’ve been to three other Frothy Monkey locations and this one was nothing like the great experiences I’ve had at the others.

The food wasn’t super over the top and they had to remake a few things. They were out of Coke, all seasonal drinks, and even the sausage and gravy… Very expensive for not being that great.
Good food in a great atmosphere. Lots of natural light.
Staff is amazing, food is even better. Most recommended!

Lovely little place with a great vibe and variety of people.
Always a favorite spot for our family.  Amazing specials, fun atmosphere and outstanding service!

Very nice atmosphere, and the bar service was great. We walked in without reservation and had to wait, but that's to be expected. The pita bread was good and hot, we got chicken shawarma and whipped feta which were both delicious!
Excellent service by Corey at a beautiful restaurant.  Food  Was great.  Go back for sure

I have eaten here multiple times with different groups of people. I truly think this is the best restaurant in Chattanooga. It’s refreshing to have an option that doesn’t serve bar food and gives diners a chance to experience cuisine from around the world. Also, the wine list is top notch.

Exceptional food, service and quantities.

We got the Sofra and an order of the octopus. The appetizer tasting was delicious (the eggplant spread of it was beyond phenomenal): it contained various spreads, olives, beats and pickled vegetables.

The second corse was the lamb shank which is GIGANTIC. It was seasoned perfectlty, fell right of the bone and served over rice. It was a really large amount.

The coarse was one of their deserts. It was perfect to end on. It was a few bites and not overly sweet.

We ordered a side of octopus. It dish was small but had a very complex flavor profile. The octopus was super tender and cooked perfectly. I highly recommend ordering.

The service was extremely quick for such a large meal. And our waiter knew the menu we'll was able to give us easy suggestions.

My only complaint was that the drinks were way too expensive. I ordered a mock tail which was essentially a coke poured over bitters and it was $8 for only 100ml! That's less than half the size of a can of soda!
Love the cocktails & ambiance

On walking in I discovered this was quite an interesting and eclectic spot for an adult beverage. They do have a very interesting selection of beverages and the patrons were even more interesting than the beverages. You get excellent service here along with the fantastic ambiance. This is a very unique and fascinating spot in Chattanooga to investigate as part of your adventures in the downtown area. Overall it is certainly one of the more unique places I have visited in the Chattanooga area.
Really cool little bar, entertaining menu and fantastic bartenders!

They charge $34.99 for 13+, $24.99 for 3-12, $5.99 for infants for sight seeing cruise. There's absolutely nothing on the cruise route that our kids are interested in. The music were garbage and too loud for the little one. The cruise ship itself needs some love. Not coming back for a second cruise with this company ever.

Valentine disaster, enjoyed the dessert before we ate the main course, the cheesecake was the best thing out of it all, prime rib wasn’t juicy to say the least, chicken was dry and overcooked, green beans were supposed to be a vibrant vegetable medley, smashed potatoes weren’t creamy at all. Enjoyed the music and the boat ride but definitely over payed for a one trip buffet that definitely didn’t deliver

We participated, with high expectation and anticipation, in the Valentine’s Day dinner cruise. The menu posted on their site highlighted a slow-roasted prime rib with “rich” flavor, a lemon basil chicken with zesty flavor, a vegetable medley full of vibrant colors, smashed potatoes that were the “ultimate comfort food”, a crisp and fresh mixed green salad, soft and golden dinner rolls, and a desert slated as the “grand finale”. My wife and I also purchased an add-on package for a charcuterie board highlighting fruits, nuts, cheeses, and meats. To begin, the prime rib delivered on its tenderness. The quality of the meat’s doneness was exquisite. However, this was overshadowed by a lack of flavor in an otherwise enjoyable piece of meat. The chicken, on the other hand, did not deliver on any of its promises. The meat was overcooked and lacked any flavor whatsoever. There was no zesty flavor, no lemon, no basil, and not even any salt or pepper. It tasted like this chicken had been blanched in a vat of hot water for too long. There were no “vibrant colors” on the selected vegetable medley. The only vegetable offered were slightly warm and crunchy green beans that were, again, lacking in any substance or flavor. The “smashed” potatoes also lacked in any richness or “comfort” as promised. At the top of the buffet tray was a pool of butter and hints of seasoning, but this was not carried throughout the remainder of the potatoes leaving a bland and gritty potato dish behind. The salad met expectations as promised. The salad offered a mix of greens including arugula, spinach leaves and romaine pieces accompanied by shredded cheese, tomatoes, and a delightful vinaigrette dressing (there was also a ranch dressing available). The dessert was another disappointing piece of this disastrous puzzle that left you bewildered and longing for better. Upon entry onto the vessel the deserts were already placed on your table setting teasing what was supposed to be the “grand finale” leaving you “smiling with every bite”. Once we had finished with the main course of the evening and moved onto dessert, we were greeted by a warm and unappealing cheesecake that had long outlived its freshness and luster. It’s possible this dessert COULD have been better had it been fresh/chilled. Overall it lacked any flavor and seemed to be a basic cheesecake. The highlight of the evening, without a doubt, was the charcuterie board. The fresh fruit paired with the flavorful cheeses and meats made this add-on a pleasant addition to the evening. In closing, after spending nearly $500 for the entirety, ($99/person, gold package add-on $99, 15% protection plan package in case of needing to cancel, and tax) I can say I left very disappointed with the overall experience. The ambiance of the boat as well as the atmosphere simply could not compensate enough to offset the disappointment of the meal. After fasting the entire day in anticipation of this wonderful and delightful evening, we were left wishing for more and regretting the decision to pay as much as we did for an experience that didn’t come close to compensating for what we paid for. I would advise against investing in this experience, and would instead advise to go and spend a fraction of the cost on an evening and experience that will produce more flavor, more interest, and more overall satisfaction.

I have never wanted to leave a bad comment so I’m not doing one star. But I honestly have never had worst sushi :( I actually think this was straight ketchup on my rolls. I boxed it up and legit fed it to a stray dog. I tried to venture out! But it did seem like there were regulars. Just beware of a “spicy tuna roll”
Amazing food, and very kind and attentive staff!
We've been going here yearly for our wedding anniversary. Today was our 5th. Always, great service. Always, great food. Hannah has been out waitress at least twice now, she's always been great too!

Valentine's Day weekend - We requested the dining room.
They seated us in an area that looked like an enclosed patio. Metal table and chairs. It felt more suitable for brunch with the girls, than a romantic dinner.
There was nothing "dining room" about it.
The tables were so close together, we could easily hear the tables around us, and you have to be careful when you pull your chair out so that you didn't ding the person behind you.
It was so loud that we could hardly hear each other speak.

From the moment we arrived we felt rushed...
All the food came out very quickly, and the waitress seemed eager to get us out of there.
It has a crowded, noisy bar environment.
It's not a romantic restaurant.
The tables are close together and it lacks intimacy.

The food was ok, it wasn't great. Mediocre at best.
We both ordered from the pasta menu...
The gnocchi wasn't light and fluffy. It was dense and burnt. The sauce was watery and loose.
The pasta was chewy and tough. The shrimp was tough, and the sauce tasted like it came out of a jar.
The meal came without bread.
With a saucy pasta dish, bread is always nice to soak up the sauce.
The dessert - the flour less chocolate cake had a texture of fudge... Hard and dense, yet melted once you played with it on your tongue.
The dessert menu was on a folded piece of old menu paper that was covered in oil splotches.

It was a disappointing experience.
It's not a fancy restaurant, it's more of a family style restaurant.
It is supposed to be one of the most romantic restaurants in the area, yet it felt like a casual dining experience with lack luster food.

Our server was outstanding and very attentive to us! She helped me pick cocktails (which was some of the best martinis I’ve had) and also helped us navigate the food menu! I would recommend this place to anyone who asked or didn’t ask honestly! Lastly, food was super flavorful and dessert was great!

This was our first time eating here so keep that in mind. This is a hard review to give because my wife and I had a different dining experience sitting across the table from each other.
I really enjoyed my meal. I had the 14oz New York strip with a loaded baked potato and it was excellent. I ordered it medium rare with garlic thyme butter and it was cooked to perfection. (See the first picture.) Whoever cooked this knew what they were doing.
However.
My wife ordered the Chilean Sea Bass with shrimp in a key lime sauce and that's where things went downhill.
The piece of fish was very small. Maybe  3 bites worth. (See second picture. The Sea Bass is right above the line on her plate.) We asked our server about it and she agreed so she called the manager. He was very nice and tried to explain they had different sizes and said they would cook another piece and would bring it out shortly. We continued eating and her meal tasted good until she got to the mushrooms. She gave some to me and they were so over seasoned they were practically inedible.
After 6-7 minutes the manager brought a second piece of fish that was the same size as the first. My wife starts to eat it and realized she couldn't cut it with her fork because it was seriously under cooked. It took 5 minutes to get anyone's attention and our server took it back to the kitchen. After another 5-6  minutes the manager brought it back and apologized again. This time the fish was flaky and tasted great. After eating the second piece my wife came to realize her first piece was probably undercooked as well. We also  ultimately figured out the Chilean Sea Bass was only supposed to be 4oz. pre cooked weight. For over $30 we expected a bigger piece of fish.
Everyone there was nice if somewhat inattentive. (It wasn't busy at all but we had a hard time getting anyone's attention.) The manager did give us a free dessert to go for all of our troubles.

And the wine they gave me was a $12 bottle from Foodlion. It was horrendously disgusting. But I guess I know next time. For sure was not a $200 steak. The picture posted is the picture they added to the advertisement.

I had dinner here Saturday night. It was pretty busy with the wait time 45 mins to an hour, so we sat at the bar for cocktails and an appetizer. The atmosphere was nice and probably would be even better in the spring or summer time with the view of the water. We sat at the end of the bar where they shucked the oysters. I ordered the “smoked” maple old fashioned, which was not smoked. But it wasnt bad. We shared the oysters bienville which I would not recommend. It was described as broiled oysters with creole crawfish sauce and andouille sausage. The oysters were raw under warm crawfish sauce and if I didnt look at the menu description again, I wouldve mistaken the andouille sausage for freezed dried beet bits. There was also extremely abrasive chunks of blue salt for some reason. But the drink gave me a nice buzz, so we continued on to dinner when we were notified our table was ready.  We were sat by the clear garage doors with a view of the water. The waiter offered a specials menu, so I ordered the roasted monkfish. It came with mashed potatoes and some sort of olive situation. It came out as one big white glob with bits of chopped up olives. I couldnt tell the difference between the mash and the fish. I think it was just reheated. It was very dry. Maybe I shouldve known because the waiter said it was a Valentine’s special menu, but it was already 2/15. I also ordered the fig and rye. It was very sweet and the syrup in it was very thick. Overall, considering the cost of it all, I wouldnt go back. It was just too costly and not very good. Disappointing because we dont go out to eat that often. We were hoping for a real treat.
We had the New York strip and LOVED it. Our server Mason was great!

Sing it on Wing it hosted my son's 10th birthday party. It was INCREDIBLE! The service was top notch, the food hot and ready, and the memories made priceless! We had about 40guests and that was a lot to keep up with. Thank you so much to the three ladies that ensured that everybody had a good time.
Jeana is the best! Will be back
Unfriendly staff.  We were excited to go until we were treated mean.
The Karaoke is fun but the sound is muffled and you can not hear the music. I told the DJ but he ignored me.

We were turned away 2 nights in a row.First cuz we had a bag of chips and sodas we wanted to take to the hotel (did not ask about ID)! Soooo we went back the next night my wife had no ID AND  we're in our 50s. So they asked us to leave! NEVER GOING BACK! IT WAS ONE OF OUR MUST DO!

I was robbed! I ordered the brisket meal, which comes with two sides. We all know that the  price of barbecue has risen significantly, but this is ridiculous. For a total of $21, you will receive two strips of brisket, approximately ¼ to ⅓ inches thick, and two sides that are likely to be approximately ⅓-¼ cup each. I WILL NEVER RETURN HERE. My family told me Memphis and Nashville are known for good q. I know why...it is because although you pay $$, they actually feed you. I literally would've gotten more meat if I went to Red Robin. Don't get me started on the taste. Brisket dry, sides taste like store bought. I guess I was so tired. After 10+ hrs of driving, I was willing to ignore the red flags: 1) staff presence was almost nonexistent for walk-in/ to-go order. I waited at the front, then the bar, and then I finally decided to go find a staff member to place my order. 2) I didn't check my food before driving back to my hotel. I just assumed this highly rated establishment would be my new fave. I learned my lesson.
Griff was such a good server, very personable and funny, definitely made our experience 100x better!
Griff was awesome!!
Griff Bundy made our experience very enjoyable!
Scrumptious truffle fries. Delicious crab bisque. Friendly staff  and excellent service.

I thought it was so lovely! Our waiter was fast and polite, our food came out within just a few minutes of ordering it, and the overall vibe was really pleasant. We had reservations, and were seated as soon as we arrived. Overall, no complaints! Everything was awesome and I'd definetly recommend
Sat at the bar for brunch , Bloody Mary was very good. The biscuits and gravy were some of the best I’ve ever

I ordered the sesame steak bowl and it was okay - verrrry salty so I could only eat about a third of it. Dessert was lovely, my friend and I split the chocolate souffle. She enjoyed her drinks a lot. Service was fine.
Fabulous food and atmosphere! Highly recommend!!
Great visit the other day! Had the Tremont burger and a Guinness. Always a great combo. ❤
Really solid bar food and friendly service. The burger is great, the wings are good, and the sweet potato fries are a standout.  The GF bun option is appreciated.
The food was kind of generic. The service was great!

My sister and I had the best experience with Megan, she’s a great server and when they didn’t have something we asked for she bent over backwards for us, and her smile was genuine and welcoming, we had a great time and we have to credit it to Megan and her service, great time, go ask for Megan

The entire staff is extremely welcoming, the food is for anyone, a lot of variety and yet I can’t find something I don’t like on the menu, it is very hard to be disappointed at UJ no matter what experience you’re looking for, go find out for yourself

One of the best spots I’ve eaten at in Chattanooga! The food was incredible. Highly recommend the sweet potato fries and the fried cheese curds. The atmosphere is great, especially when it’s warm enough to sit outside on the patio and soak up some sun. The service was top notch too! I had Megan Joana Pence as my server—she was awesome, remembered my drink order like a mind reader. Definitely coming back again because who wouldn't want another round of those sweet potato fries?

Terrible service.  We were there to celebrate 2 birthdays, our server was not there after taking our order, we had to ask other servers for help. Then she appeared with our bill while we were still eating, never asking it we wanted dessert. Don't waste your time and money here
We had Valentine’s dinner here and it was wonderful. Trinity served us and she is an absolute sweetie and the food was so amazing!
Best restaurant in Chattanooga! All the servers are great but Ana is the best!!! They are always so accommodating and friendly. The service is 12/10! Highly highly recommend!!

This is hands down my FAVORITE restaurant in Chattanooga. The service, the staff, the food, all AMAZING! This is the best steak I have ever had anywhere. Ana is always great with meal suggestions and modifications!

My husband and I went to Zaya for the first time to celebrate Valentine’s Day. They had a special menu which was $149 a person. The food was amazing but we both agreed that it was not worth the price. As customers spending over $400 that evening, we did have high expectations and ran into several issues. The bathroom was not well kept (mystery liquids on the floor), we had to box our own food and the dessert was missing things mentioned on the menu. Don’t get me wrong we would definitely go here again but just for a date night where the pricing is ~50$ a person.

Michael provided excellent service from start to finish. A very wonderful experience throughout and great food as well. If you go here make sure to ask for Michael as your server. The steak frites were cooked perfectly and the brownie with the ice cream was delicious. Ask for strawberries as well to go with it adds an eccentric touch to the meal.
Wait and service can be extremely slow at times, but the food is always worth it!!! I love the country cuban as well as the steak frites. Sangria flights on Thursday are a great deal!

This restaurant deserves more than 5 stars!!! Everything was top notch, the food, the service and the charming patio.  Here at last is a chef who knows how to cook salmon. Absolute perfection!!! The grilled vegetables,  were just that, grilled and tasty and their feta scallion mash potatoes are legendary.  The entire meal was a delight, and something I rarely say, was worth every penny I paid. Can't wait to come back!
Why say you're open around 12 when it's just the cigar area... Hours should be updated to show when food and pool are actually available. What a waste of time and parking fees.

Pool tables are ... PERFECTLY FOR Game sss
Service staff is above that. Normal...looking .,.FOR APA..THIS IS THE PLACE
IT CAN be smokie in the environment at times...but if one can put up with this......as pool playing can BE Sometimes then up stairs is the PLACE..

“We gave your debit card to someone else, do you have another way to pay for your tab?”

Had a great time at CBC. The staff was great. The debit card used to start my tab was given to someone else. When this came to my attention, the establishment requested I provide another form of payment. A manager was requested and I was forced to call 911.

The manager Tony, said I was being a dick.

There is a public 911 call to listen to.
Awesome atmosphere and playlist
Mitchell was a great bartender! Try the Hot Mama, Kolsch with habenero and green pepper!

Drew is the best! I am a strict neat bourbon drinker, but he made me the best bourbon mixed drink. The single dad! Ha! He also made my picky ass mom a drink she would like. He is so kind, and will mix cocktails to your taste. Come here!!!
8 min with no one recognizing me, and there was no one at the bar.  Once acknowledged it too 5 min for her to ask for my order.  The bar tender was a zero
Love the waiter alcohol drinks on point salsa is amazing and just outstanding service love you guys!!
Jennifer was the best! Great customer service, and got everything right. We will be returning to this location because of her.
Awesome place great food too

Have to give a shout out to Hannah V. as a server and Nate, the cook! Hannah was fast and courteous. When I asked if I could pay extra for additional seasoning on my Cajun Chicken Pasta, Hannah immediately said yes. When I saw what was presented to me, I had to ask who cooked it. MAJOR props to Nate in the kitchen for knowing what EXTRA seasoning means. Will be back because of these two showing outstanding customer service.
This trip to Chili's was horrible it took the food forever to get to us and it was not good I will not be back to this Chili's again
Really good pizza, nice interior and surrounding area, service was nice, and the options all sounded good. A little pricey for the food but that doesn't mean it wasn't great.

We were recommended to try this place by a hotel staff member during our stay. The wait to get in was relatively quick but everything else was extremely slow. We ordered cheese sticks for a appetizer and they didn't come out until after our pizzas arrived (which took about 40 minutes to get) by that point we didn't even really want them anymore but they set them down anyways and said sorry about the wait time on those. Our waiter checked on us about 3 times total. The pizza was okay but not worth the wait. We probably wouldn't go back.
Food was very good as well as the service.   Always has good atmosphere.   Will head back for sure.
One of the best pizza places I’ve ever been to in Tennessee! Each time we have exceptional service and fantastic food.
Great experience!

Came in from Atlanta to see the aquarium and Edleys was recommended on Tik Tok and IG. Greeted soon as I walked in (love that) Everyone is so pleasant and the food was really really good lots of flavor and not too pricey. That Brisket is 10 outta 10. Definitely will come again!

I called a few weeks ago as a dasher to get an order placed and was told they were so busy that they couldn't place the order when I got there to pick up the dash i was assigned to, there were three tables in the whole store took me 6 mins to get there  today  came in to get a dash asked about a soup or stew was told by bartender had brisket stew told him I'll get that he walks away to tend to a bar guest then I wait and asked another gentleman he said it's seasonal he doesn't know if they have it this is not good service even if I am a dasher I still deserve to be served or be given proper answers
This place is absolutely outstanding! Their food is great, the staff is so friendly and on top of everything. Me and my husband have the best experience every time we go. Highly recommend!
Blanca is an excellent server
If you want cold dry meat with no salsas, lime, on corn tortillas order the street tacos. Best part was the queso and chips. 40 bucks for 6 tacos and chips and queso is diabolical
Great food - service was slightly off due to being busy on the day after Valentine’s Day -the pork scallopini was awesome

Had a wonderful dinner at Il Primo on a Saturday evening. We were lucky and got in around 5:15pm right before an influx of other diners began pouring in.

The food was absolutely delicious and our server Jacob was friendly and great throughout our entire experience. While I didn't have any complaints on the entrees nor the portions, I feel like was the real star of the meal was the arancini telefono which we ordered as our starter.

While the meal was a bit pricier than I expected it to be, I feel like it was worth it for the quality of the food and service. I think Il Primo is a great place for a date night and will definitely be coming back.
10pm on a saturday. they say they have been closed since 9. all those facilities wasted. been here a few times. ghost town always and service not too good. decide if you want to be open or closed.

Food was ok. The place was pretty empty. Smelled like paint walking in. The bartender was painting the bar during business hours.

Burgers looked good but everything else was just ok.

I never write reviews but I don't want anyone to have the same experience my family did. We had a group of 5 adults and 2 children. We went for the first & LAST time on Sunday 12/22, when we arrived only 1 group was seated and they left shortly after we arrived so we were the only group eating. I asked a blonde woman wearing a blue hoodie that was working at the bar if we order at the bar or have a seat and she just replied you can. She did not smile or seem to want us there, I asked what she recommended food wise and she said I don't know, so I said that's ok and ordered then found a table to sit at. The rest of my family ordered and were rudely told that we ordered the rest of their burgers so now they are out. We waited a long time for our food and a younger woman brought it out, she was nice but our food was cold and she told us she didn't know what was what. Another woman with red hair started working at the bar and was the only one who made us feel welcome, she was very friendly and helpul. I went to the bar and ordered another drink and the blonde woman gave me and my sister the wrong drinks but we didn't say anything due to her attitude. We asked if the gift shop was open and were told no because someone left early. Before we left, my daughter asked where the bathroom was and a group of staff and an older man sitting at the bar said right in front of you, you are walking right towards it then started whispering to one another. We smiled and remained friendly despite how we were treated and told them all to have a good evening and a Merry Christmas. The blonde just stood there looking mad and the red head replied and was again very friendly. Later that night we were all sick and kept having to go to the bathroom.
Great location for pictures decent food and clean bathrooms

I didn't eat there so it's a 1 for not knowing. The service was the worst I've seen in quite some time. 3 bartenders behind the bar and not a 1 of them knew what the word hustle means! I stood waiting for drinks for 20+minutes and never got them and this was right before midnight on New Years Eve. Horrible service and everyone of them needs replaced because they are not right for that job!! Thought that was how great bartenders made amazing money by getting it done behind the bar and getting nice tips because they are recognized for there work!! These 3 acted like they should get paid for just being there and literally watching paint dry would be more exciting!!!
Great location! Westin Village is bright and inviting! The rooftop bar has fireplaces and comfortable seating!
We only visited the place to hang in the lounge area and have a drink. Plenty of people here, great ambiance.

We were so excited to try this restaurant since we love tapas but it wasn't a great experience. It took a long time for someone to come to our table initially. Around 15 minutes. She took our order but didn't write anything down. 10 minutes later she came back and asked us to repeat the order but still never wrote anything down. After 40 minutes, we got one of the tapas we ordered. We never got our drinks the whole time we were there, despite reminding the server several times. We just had water but really wanted to try the cocktails we ordered but never got. Second and third tapas arrived about 20 minutes after the first. Food was AMAZING and couldn't have been better. We wanted to order more but didn't dare try. The one server that seemed to be working every table kept walking up to tables with plates of food and asking if this was their order. The place is beautiful. Super short staffed though, and that definitely affects the experience. Would love to go back, but not for a repeat of this visit. Everyone was nice but they are clearly overwhelmed.

reviews.text: Great service and fun family experience! Kimberly was wonderful as our server.

Angel was a fantastic server.

Jimmy understood his assignment and gave me the perfect amount of meat each time.

I’ve been to this restaurant several times but this last time was terrible! We went there the day after Valentine’s Day around 7pm. There was a 45 minute wait time. We ordered alcoholic beverages and was disappointed with the taste and the margarita wasn’t even all the way filled. I don’t want to ever try a Long Island Ice Tea bc no one can make it right. It was very sour yuck. We didn’t get to try all the meat that was going around maybe bc they stuck us in one of the back rooms. I don’t think we will be back again it’s not worth the price for such terrible service. So basically our Valentines dinner was a flop this year maybe next year we can go to Outback or somewhere’s else that we can get out moneys worth.

My boyfriend and I went there on Valentines day. We had a reservation for 8:00.

We got there at 7:30 to check in and was told to come back at 8:10. We come back at this time and are told it is a 30-45 minute wait past our reservation time. At this point we go and sit at the bar.

The bartenders were extremely disappointing. It appeared that there were only two bartenders making cocktails for everyone in the entire establishment for tonight. That seems like poor planning on managements side for a night like Valentine's day. It took over 20 minutes to get someone's attention. I had to ask for a menu twice just for a customer to bring me one because the bartenders were that busy.

One bartender was obviously too stressed and emotional to accommodate patrons in a meaningful manner. They were loudly complaining about how busy the night was and how stressed out they were. Well, it's Valentine's Day. That is one of the busiest nights of the year for nicer restaurants.

When we finally got our names called for our reservation, 45 minutes later, we actually were taken out of the restaurant, and into what appeared to be the adjoining hotel's conference room to have dinner there.

At that point, my boyfriend and I were extremely disappointed and contemplated leaving. The dining area was set up like a seminar hall for work conferences.

Very embarrassing and disappointing for a restaurant that advertises good service & dining expectations. Never have I been to a restaurant and they've seated me into another establishment, a conference room for that matter. That was a first experience.

We sat down at a table (at the hotel conference room, not the restaurant) that was so unleveled and unbalanced that putting a plate on it would cause a drink to knock over. We asked our waiter to fix it and he didn't so my boyfriend shoved a napkin under the leg of the table so it would at least stay upright.

Before I sat down into my chair there was actually food on the chair and I had it swapped out. Our waiter gave us our drinks. The straw that finally broke the camels back was when we actually saw the meat come out on skewers, and how awful it looked.

At this point we got up and left and went to Taco Mac. If anyone asks me about this place, this is the experience I will tell them about. I probably would've had a better experience in a sit down Krystal. Taco Mac did a great job taking care of us.
Great service and great food!
The staff was very attentive, and the food was wonderful. Enjoyed the family together and staff, too, made it a great dining experience.
Other than the fact that a location next to boathouse in chatt this place is the bomb. Service, food and atmosphere is dynamite!  I his is a pricey upscale place but worth every cent.

Dined here around 4:30 on 2/15 and the service and food was awesome. Our server brought us a ipad with pictures and full ingredient list of the menu items. I had the Garlic Crusted Sea Bass and the Spicy Shrimp as an appetizer. Bother were delicious and I would order again.

Overall a great experience and will definitely return in the future.

This was my second time eating at this specific location and they always do a fantastic job. Our waiter tonight was Violet and she did such a good job attending to our needs and even recommended so much good food. She suggested the Cupids Arrow drink and I am so glad she did! It was delicious and went well with my food. Food came out at a good manner of time and everything was fresh and juicy! Def 10/10 and Violet made our time there very comfortable and enjoyable.
Jordan was our server and he was amazing.  He provided top notch service.  The restaurant is a little pricey but the food is always great.  My steak was cooked to perfection.

Quite frankly, we were disappointed with the experience. We ordered two vegetarian tacos. One of them was vegetarian and the other had ham in the stuffing. The staff was nice enough not to charge us and gave us free food coupon for the mistake. We were looking forward to a nice experience as this was the first place we went to when we visited Chattanooga for a short stay. The ambiance was great and the staff were nice !
Mamacita bel grande nah mean
Great food at a good price
Been here a few times & enjoyed their tacos.

A+ food, the avocado jalapeno margarita is to die for. And the bartending staff is always excellent. They remember your name and what you like to order and they're always so friendly. This is our weekly go to spot.
Cool spot, service was really good. We love that they always have Calf Killer on tap!
Great stop for lunch, with a large draft beer menu and a good variety on the food menu. The Trout Spread is amazing (pairs well with a good IPA)
Great beer and awesome staff. Their pretzel and beer cheese is a must!!

Excellent selection of beers on tap, with regular rotation to new ones.  The staff is pretty well informed as to what most of the beers are like, and willing to provide a small sample upon request.  Food is quite good, with a selection of apps, burgers, sandwiches and salads available.  They host trivia, have happy hours, and occasional special events.  The owner is a vet, and very gracious and knowledgeable about beers from around the world.  We really enjoy going here!

REAL IDS TURNED DOWN BY EMOTIONAL MANAGER: SENT OUT WARNING TO SURROUNDING EATERIES!
My friends and I (from Louisiana,) are visiting Tennessee and decided to stop at Urban Stack for our Chattanooga munchies. Our waitress took our order of a carafe of wine to start, and proceeded to tell us the manager would need to take a look at our IDS to validate them.
Ten minutes later, Manager Lila took her time, picked up an attitude, to come back  and tell us that the IDS read invalid and that one of them was even broken!

Instead we went to HiFi Clyde’s (5 stars. Right down the street. Same parking) and our IDS were magically validated.

Maybe she was at the end of her shift, maybe she just put her dog down. But manager Lila will not be seeing us again. She was over us from the beginning. Felt unwelcome
Nice restaurant, the staff was friendly and knowledgeable, great food
Went here last July for dinner. Pretty solid burger and the beer is good. Staff is nice. Good dining experience.
Best burger joint. Potato skins were ok just wish I would have known about all the toppings would have sided them
Besides a rotten strawberry on my wife’s French toast it was okay. Not really worth a stop unless you’re starving
Great deserts!
Good joint adjacent to BW
I got the southwest quesadilla rolls and they tasted great! Our waitress was kind and efficient. Very standard diner experience.
Great place and very kid friendly. My children really enjoyed it
I've had better...

Great little place with homemade tasting food. Service is excellent. Very low-cost lunch specials that give great value for the money. They even have a sizable meeting space for your parties or organizations.
For a neighborhood pizzeria this place was legit!  Wood fired ovens that gave this local joint a true Italian experience!  Next time I’m in Chattanooga I will definitely go again!
Great neopolitan pizza.
We love Fiama! We live in North Atlanta area but anytime we’re in Chattanooga we stop for some pizza. They have the BEST gluten free pizza I’ve ever had.
They had a playlist better than most nightclubs I’ve been to but was also kid appropriate.  Had me ready to go to the club but I had to go home and do my taxes.  Food was great
Love this place! Our family's go to.....

We made reservations for a group of 15. We arrived on time and waited 20 minutes to be seated. 45 minutes in we watched as many families after us had been through their habachi show and we were still waiting. The food was just ok. The atmosphere just ok. Probably won’t come back.
Good and derived was phenomenal
Got cut of at 3 beeers
Horrible customer service didn’t even get greeted by the server
We had the best service ever &  the food was absolutely amazing. When you get there ask for Kyra, she won’t let ya down!!

Hailey was awesome. It was a somber day since my best friend passed away last year and we met once a month for lunch there. Hailey sat and listened. Then she got other customers and did her thing and came back checking on me. My best friends daughter came that day, and Hailey made sure we were taken care of.
An awesome staff  helped pull offa birthday surprise joke.

Elegant and welcoming environment.
Excellent service with professional and friendly staff.
Advised.

I've probably spent $10,000 at this restaurant. I rolled in with guests tonight and they were out of filet, the substitute offering was terrible, we sat on the patio for probably 15 minutes before I had to go IN and find someone. If chains are your gig, you can do better.  Not even close to what this restaurant used to be 5 years ago. No doubt you can feel the pressure of not being able to hire quality people, literally as soon as you sit down. That's cool at Burger King but not we're going to drop $100 a person. Hard stop on this brand for me.  Update 2/2025. Just buy bumblebee

Always has very good CONSISTENT, food and service. Can tell the wait staff is well trained and always quick service. Steps of service are always tight, and there is a good balance of getting food quickly but not feeling rushed. We like to come here for anniversaries and birthdays and are never disappointed. No criticism here. Keep up the good work.
Excellent experience. Great food, incredible coffee, and a competent server.

We chose this restaurant for a special Valentine’s dinner, but unfortunately, the experience fell far short of expectations. The outdoor seating was uncomfortably cramped, making it difficult to have a conversation without feeling like we were intruding on others. My wife and I barely spoke because the setup was just that uncomfortable.

The food was the biggest disappointment. The steak was so dry that my wife nearly choked, and I was moments away from having to step in—this is not an exaggeration. The potatoes, green beans, and lobster were also overcooked and dry, with the only redeeming item on the plate being the corn. It genuinely seemed like the steak had been sitting on a hot plate for far too long before being served.

Despite the poor experience, I paid the $194 tab and left without making a fuss. I wasn’t looking for a free meal, even though I noticed the table next to us did. I truly expected better for a special occasion, and unfortunately, this was one of the most disappointing dining experiences I’ve had.

A friend and I were downtown Chattanooga eating and decided to look up a wine tasting place near by and found this spot. We didn’t look at the reviews before we decided togo. When we first pulled up we notice that all the outside seating was fold up tables and chairs like we just came to a family reunion. Then we notice that the view was very nice. We order the flight of wine. Great price until you get it and realize it’s not even half of once to taste. Wine tasted like chemicals. Not sure if that’s how it supposed to taste or what but I never had wine taste like before and I’ve had plenty of dry wines. We didn’t try the pizza. I personally wouldn’t go back or recommend.

The waitress was very nice, but the wines were extremely bitter and tasted old like they were turning into vinegar. She tried saying they weren't sweet because there's no added sugar, but they tasted oxidized. She was heavy to push the pizza but we decided to eat elsewhere so I can't comment on food quality.

My husband and I stopped here on the way to Chatt. So glad we did. Just found one of our new favorite pizzas. Before we had to go to Dough Pizzeria in San Antonio to get a proper pizza. The wine was also amazing. Not that sweet sugary stuff you get at most of the semi-local wineries within driving distance to Middle Tn. We left with 3 bottles. Each had a flavor combination we’ve never had before. Our server was very informative about the menu and our options and was very attentive our whole time there. The owner came out and talked to us about his family and recipes. We will definitely be back soon.
Best vegan pizza in the Cleveland area!!

very disappointed with the place and surprised by the good reviews. everything around is very dusty, dust falls from the lamps right on the food. there is no paper menu, something is scribbled on the wall. instead of plates there are some scratched shabby, greasy trays, the table is dirty, the staff is untidy, the price tag is too high for such pizza and place. the beer is terrible. no choice. we will never go there again and do not advise anyone to order pizza and eat under terribly dusty lamps, from just a breath dust falls right on the pizza, the check is not less than 65 dollars for 4. horror(
The best pizza and calzones!
I always visit this pizza place when I visit town. I like that it is close to the aquarium and they are super accommodating to food sensitivities. The food portions are very large.
Lupi's is the best pizza in town, & everyone that works there is awesome!
Just what I was looking for while passing through.  Very good.

Pizza in general lately has been pretty disappointing everywhere we have gone until tonight! SO GOOD! Fresh hot plenty of toppings and real ooey gooey mozzarella cheese! We both were so happy. Also $3.00 PBR drafts. The staff was attentive and so pleasant. It is rare you sit and watch all the workers completely busy even when they didn’t have a customer. Wiping cleaning stocking and checking on tables. This was just the best experience. Music was perfect too! Great job Lupis
Tasty food and a cool vibe - I love coming here with friends.
Very hospitable service. The food is fresh and delicious, as always.

Haven't been to this Olive Garden in a few years and we had a hundred-dollar gift card from the holidays so we decide to see if anything's changed or not in terms of food quality and wait staff. We ordered a seafood alfredo and a chicken carbonara. Our waiter came to the table numerous times to check up on us which was great and our drinks were constantly refilled. We had zero issues at this location and everything was simply perfect. We went during the lunch time hours of 12 to 1:00 p.m. and it wasn't terribly busy which was a plus for us.
Excellent food and service.

We were celebrating my mother in law's 89th birthday at OG - one of her favorite places. Although the restaurant wasn't busy, the service was very, very slow. What's worse, 3 wait staff were standing next to us complaining about another coworker so loudly that we were basically pulled into their drama of someone's chicken alfredo being taken by another waiter to a table that had been waiting less time. Our server was really nice but it was just overall a tacky, tacky, experience. Thank goodness my mother in law can't hear worth a darn or it may have affected her experience.

We just had Sabrina as our server and it was the best server both of us have ever had. She was constantly encouraging refills for everything and making sure we were taken care of. She was so sweet and made us feel like we were in her home.
Delicious food at reasonable prices. I had the shrimp scampi light meal. The service Personnel are very friendly and attentive to your needs. Their take-home meals for $6 is a plus.

I have a gift card for $50. I was trying to put in an order for takeout for my family and it come out to $58. I couldn’t use my gift card and pay the difference because my gift card didn’t cover the entire amount. So then I called in to try and place my order. I got an automated message telling me to place to-go orders online. So… looks like Longhorn Steakhouse is getting my $50 gift card and I will continue to avoid Olive Garden as I have done my entire life. Hopefully the day will come when big businesses remember that getting repeat business happens when the customer experience is pleasant and not an inconvenience. I know Mr. Olive Garden doesn’t care, but I feel better after leaving a 1-star review. If Mr. Olive Garden would like to talk about it he’ll need to submit a ticket online to my personal time website or call into my automated personal time hotline.

Restaurant slow, hostess talking when we walked in, took a bit to be noticed. We were sat across from another table even though the restaurant was bare. Our waitress was so Rude. Our soup was room temp and she said there is nothing she can do about it. The salad was good like always. Just disappointed, felt as though the restaurant has went down in appeal.
Coffee and food was really enjoyable, and they had a lot of classic options mixed with more unique ones. Not much indoor seating, and was super busy when I went, but the food was great overall.

super adorable atmosphere! the chocolate scone and tomato artichoke soup were both genuinely some of the most delicious foods i’ve ever eaten. the service was incredibly fast despite the place being crazy busy. i’d give this place 6 stars if i could.
Great spot to stop for coffee in Chattanooga.

Honestly amazing every time. The coffee and teas are always great and are the right temperature. The staff is fun and calm, they match energy easily and well. If you have any questions they are easy to talk to and never give attitude.

Host was slightly condescending, didn't seem keen on our group walking in with a baby. However, the wait staff was above and beyond polite and even stopped to entertain the baby in our group for a moment. They kept the food coming! Everything was melt in your mouth tender and we enjoyed our experience very much. An excellent place for a grownup birthday party.
Great place my favorite
Gilberto was our server.   Extremely polite, helpful.    Food was Great!
10/10 experience for Valentine’s day! Great service from Andres!
Got the Labneh, grouper sandwich, and Shrimp Tacos
Excellent food excellent views a place to be calm & service was great.

Not a good experience at all. Our server was not making our experience any better. Very slow service, our server was not friendly at all  and the menu is too expensive for a poolside cafe. Charged 16$ for a plain hotdog for kids! Oh, and valet only - and didn’t inform us that it would be $16 to park! Won’t be back to Skyside. Love McClemore but not this place.

Worst dining experience I have had in a long time. Service was slow, not accommodating, and overall bad. Will not be back. Oh, and it is valet only and there is an automatic $16 charge to retrieve your car. But they will not warn you of that!
The place is filthy!

We had a birthday party and EVERYTHING was OVERCHARGED based on what the prices were online. They were EXTREMELY RUDE when we asked if adults could bowl and basically told us that it's a kid party and adults shouldn't be bowling at a kids party. Then after looking at the receipt,  they over charged us for 5 kids. And when I called to see if they could give a partial refund for that overpayment, I was YELLED AT by the owner and told that I was the problem because I didn't keep up with how many kids checked in at the front desk. They are the absolute rudest people that I've ever felt with. Never in my life have I been yelled at after being ripped off by a business.

RESPONSE TO THE OWNERS REPLY:

I asked multiple times how many kids checked in to the party to get shoes and was told you weren't sure. I quite obviously gave up and said "whatever you have counted that attended" and was told you didn't have the number down for the kids that showed up. And I told you that we used the 3rd lane for 1 extra kid and put a few others to bowl that lane as well as on the other lanes. And you knew that 4 went home which is why we used the same 10 kids per Lazer tag game. And yes I got upset and cursed at you because you were yelling over me and I couldn't get a word on. THAT IS NOT CUSTOMER SERVICE!  Respect is a big thing and you nor the rude man up front have any of that at all. And I was told you couldn't break down the package but the package was completely broken up on the receipt. It literally says 14 bowling 14 Lazer tag,  28 pizza which was actually only 2 pizzas at 55.00 and then the other 2 pizzas were 27.00 then you charged 60.99 gratuity that was not mentioned ANYWHERE until due. Not to mention the fact that we were supposed to get invitations with that package. Never got those. And each child was supposed to get a free game of future bowling and when I asked about that on the phone you said you didn't do that bc your business is closing Friday. That was never mentioned, and that would have given the kids 6 days to go redeem their coupon. But you just decided against even giving those at all even though I paid almost 500 for a party that was priced at 280.00
But the most frustrating part of the situation is the way you handle your customers concerns. Yelling at them on the phone is completely unprofessional and you deserve to go out of business for screwing people over!

the fact that i came in here with my friends all to be cussed out by the dude behind the counter because he can’t hear. we told him it was 3 adults and a baby then proceeded to yell at us because we asked for the baby shoes and he said “YOU DIDNT TELL ME YOU WERE PAYING FOR THE BABY, TELL ME NEXT TIME” like who did you think was paying for the baby? he also yelled at the people next to us bc they wanted a water. i will never come back with how trashed the place was and the rudeness from the employees. i cannot believe he would literally act that way. do better.

I was there for a corporate event. For the most part, it's a pretty fun place. It's large with plenty of bowling lanes and an arcade.
The main rooms are clean and well lit. On the other hand, the ladies restroom is cramped and uncomfortable. It could have used a good cleaning.
They were also out of a popular soda, Dr pepper, at 3:30 on a Friday afternoon.
Family friendly, clean bowling area, automatic gutter rails so kids don't have to have a separate lane or constantly pull them up. Pretty good size arcade area as well and Great prices
So much fun!
Hands down Best BBQ in Chattanooga that I have tried

First time I’ve eaten here and I feel compelled to share how delicious the food was. I had beef tacos and they were perfectly seasoned, not one ingredient overpowered another and when I say perfectly served- right down to the presentation, perfect. Definitely worth eating at once a week in rotation! The server was so kind and considerate, super friendly and we didn’t have to run her down. To top it all off, the manager, Zach- he greeted us when we came in, seated us and told us a bit about the restaurant. He came back later to check on us, too. Again, real friendly, funny, knowledgeable and considerate. Atmosphere is an all around great feeling and any sports you happen to be watching will be on one of their wall to wall tvs! Since it was my first time, they gave me a free dessert of pure sinful flavor! My goodness, y’all must come eat here. My husbands burger was top 3 burgers in Chattanooga, hands down. Fabulous experience- fabulous staff, which can only mean that the manager Zach has created a very special place to eat. Thanks Taco Mac
Still one of my favorite places! Best brussel sprouts on the planet!
Decided to get a lunch here,waited for an hour for burger and fries
Always great wings everytime.
Great shawarma
Reliably good food and fast service, friendly too!
Love the lemon chicken soup!  Food is always great every time we visit.
Great casual atmosphere, food prices a little high, but food was excellent!
Great meal food fresh and hot

Brought my daughter here for lunch.  They do great with ensuring a gluten-free meal for my daughter.  Service was pretty quick from when we placed our order to when we received our food.  Nice relaxing environment.  It wasn't overly crowded when we visited, so that was enjoyable.  Overall a good experience!

The sandwiches were good, but service took a really long time (one sandwich showed up after everyone else was done) without any apology. The staff were also strangely dismissive of my wife’s questions. I also did not realize the 12 tribes cult affiliation when I chose this restaurant and will not be back given stories of abuse from people who have left. I would advise anyone considering eating here to do their research and know who you are patronizing beforehand.
Great place to eat if you are not in a hurry. People who work there are great. Food is excellent.
Good food. Atmosphere is very cute and welcoming. Our waiter wasn’t as attentive a few weeks ago as he needed and didn’t listen to my nit allergy. Thankfully he fixed it quickly

100% recommend this place. The people are lovely, food is nice, beverages are incredibly interesting (Maté, matcha and more).

The kindness from the people is rare to see, I felt very welcome.

The place is beautiful, attention to details is everywhere. Open amazingly 24h a day; it is a super comfy place.

Would recommend!
Good food and service!
Deserts look great.  Yummy

I visited with my family on Sunday  2/16/25, We had the worst experience  with poor food quality  I have ever experienced. Our server was very good and attentive, Tge manager passed us 4 times after I sent my foid back and did not stop to ask if everything  was corrected properly. I will never return  to this location.
Loved the servers and the food was pretty damn good🙈

We came here years ago and food was good, but we both thought quality of sushi and hibachi has definitely dropped. Over cooked my filet which tasted awful, shrimp was dry, veggies not cooked and was smallest portion I had ever received. Not sure what dressing was on the salad, tasted like a mayo base? Atmosphere was dull besides the robot and the hibachi chef seemed like he hated his job. Save yourself the money and try somewhere else. This place needs an overhaul.
Absolutely phenomenal food with a super friendly staff. My husband and I went here for lunch.
We celebrated my birthday and the food was great! I loved the robot who came out to sing me Happy Birthday.

BEST sushi and hibachi experience in Chattanooga, Tennessee!
VERY REASONABLE PRICES AND EXCELLENT FRESH FOOD AND  GREAT SERVICE!
HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!
Must try!

I was disappointed with what I received for the price I paid. We were charged $27 for two affogatos with dairy free ice cream and they were fine, but not $27 fine. I can’t really speak for their ice cream which honestly could have been incredible, but the affogatos just weren’t it for me.
Great experience the gentleman upfront was kind! Try the banana pudding flavor
Still the best in Chatt
A city staple of Chattanooga.  Love this place!
Great place for soups, salads, and sandwiches.  This place never fails on having food food.
We absolutely love Jason’s Deli! Especially in the last few months the service and food have been amazing, both when eating in and when ordering online. Wish we had one in Hixson…
California Club is my favorite!!

Ordered the tuna melt sandwich. It was definitely NOT up to Jason's standards. There was no "melt." The cheese was just a cold slice of cheese and the sandwich was cold. "Melt" implies ... something  melted!

The pinnacle of prefect!
I loved it. The vibe the volume the feeling the food and drinks.
Super amazing and so lovely!!
Very cool atmosphere amazing. Amazing food was great. Drinks was great. The service was great.
Good luck here.  Staff is not friendly and drinks stink. If it's late and you're hungry, Taco Bell is the better option.

Don’t trust them to seat you even if you have a reservation. We arrived about 40 minutes before our 9:30 reservation, not worried about being sat early. We left at 9:50 after minimal acknowledgement from who appeared to be the front desk staff as they said “it was slammed.” I would not recommend this for people who value their time or staff at least respecting them enough to maintain an open line of actual professional communication.
Awesome pizza!
Omg! Amazing food and service. Loved it! Will def stop by again. The toppings were fresh and plentiful, and the calzone is huge! Highly recommend! 🍕
The food here was so good, my wife and I genuinely considered moving to Chattanooga from Huntsville. The arrachera is ridiculously good. So grateful we came here.
The food was great and our server, Zoey, was incredible! Will definitely return the next time we are in this area!
Kinda pricey but the food is great
Love going here for date nights. A little dressy. AMAZING food. The Hanger steak is the best. Also the the Ropa veiga is good. I love the sweet plantains are delicious. Will be back again

First employees were very nice…. People running the place are terrible it already closed will close again screwed me on a coupon then I get home a massive hair in my food place is dirty not sanitary do not go there!!!!! Chipotle is not ight across the street.

This is my go-to restaurant when I’m around the mall because I like the menu and it’s always fresh.   Also  the new decor is quite nice and super clean- looks great.
Tonight (feb 3) around 8:00 I went in and had a burrito made to go.    The young lady (who had braided hair)  was exceptionally nice and polite and is a stand-out employee.  Your staff is always great but she was a bright spot in my day.
Always a great place !
Moe's has lost touch. Way overpriced and shrinking portions everytime. A $2.99 uncharge for steak. I won't return. There are too many other options.
Not sure when Moe's became such a rip off ...$15 for this tiny bowl and thank goodness they only gave me a few chips, because they were stale and tasted like spoiled oil.
Family friendly, pizza and breadsticks were great. Personal pizza is bigger than what it shows.
Great pizza, fun atmosphere!

I grew up in East Tennessee and went to one of these in Knoxville in the 1990’s after over 20 yrs out of the area when I saw this restaurant was still in business I was thrilled and so excited the day I picked up dinner for my family here, but also afraid it couldn’t live up to my memories - IT DID!
The rolls and salad were as delicious as we all remembered and they sent plenty! The Mushroom Cannelloni was as richly cheesy and wonderful as remembered and I have never found anything like it elsewhere. We enjoyed everything and will be back for more.

Have been coming here for years and was extremely disappointed this time. The food was not up to par. Alfredo sauce was EXTREMELY BLAND. Asked for fresh grated Parmesan and was handed dried Parmesan in a shaker. There was a winged bug in my sweet tea. I brought this to the attention of my server who said she would replace it. I waited over ten minutes to get a replacement tea. Shocking really.  I do have to say that the server was really great at the beginning and very sweet about checking in on us often. I think she just ended up really busy when we were waiting for the replacement glass of tea.
I eat there 4 times a year and normally love chicken broccoli Alfredo.  I hate how dry the chicken is,  but I always give it a another try. What should I do to improve the situation
Robbie, our server was excellent on our VDay date night. Food was delicious. We can't wait to Revisit and try some more great food
The food was really good, and the drinks were great.  They didn't have a kids menu, though.
Savannah is the most awesome server
The menu is full of indulgent options that cater to everyone. The red curry chicken was some of the best seasoned I've had in a long time. So glad our friends recommended this place to us!
Great food and overall place !!!
The best lasagna I have eaten. The bread is delicious and I love the way they cool the garlic into the bread. Such a good experience. We will be back.
Great expeirence- wonderful food and atmosphere. Always a pleasure.

We’ve been going to Tony’s for years and have never been disappointed. Today we went for Valentines Day and I had their special, Salmone e Gamberetto Saltati
(Grilled Salmon and Sautéed Shrimp over Roasted Fingerling Potatoes & Asparagus with a Garlic Shallot Cream Sauce). Wow!  That just may be one of the best meals I’ve ever had. If you haven’t been, you must give Tony’s a try. The food is always good, nice casual vibe, and the service is great. It is our favorite place to go.
The food is disgusting and overpriced.
Very friendly staff! Chewie was very fast and helpful! Food is good for a quick bite to eat. Would recommend swinging by before or after the gardens. Thank you Rock City!

I expected a little more of a fancy spot since it was located inside of rock city gardens but it was still worth the stop. They have “cirrhosis fries” if you know what I’m talking about. If not, they’re the best fries you can get.
Food isn't too bad,  service is mid, read your recipts, this is one of those places that will say a cheeseburger is 15.99 and then charge you an extra buck for the cheese -_-
You had to ask for and pay extra for the cheese on a menu item named "cheeseburger." Otherwise, it's exactly how you remember this pllace from your childhood
This is one of the best places to eat at.  We have never had a bad meal or service there. If you ever have a chance to go there, do so.

Have eaten here before but was very disappointed this visit. Entre was undercooked and appitizer over cooked. The dessert was excellent! It just seemed las though every table was trying to talk over the next. Noisy
Every time we take friends to dinner, it is always great at Canyon Grill.  The service is fantastic and the food is awesome. We never get disappointed at #canyongrill.
The history on Chattanooga whiskey was very educational and and earn your sticker after tasting with their survey
Really enjoyed this place! Fun your, nice flights, cool building. Lots to choose from. We got a regular flight and a vault flight, and they have great old fashioned syrup. Ethan was very helpful!

What a great place! Stopped in right before closing and chatted with Ali about their whiskeys as was able to taste a couple of their offerings. Everything was awesome and Ali helped me pick up a great bottle!
Very nice people. And the tour was interesting.  Whiskey was great, and their single Rye was good too.
Justin was awesome! Great spot
Bland steak had to ask for refills

Walked in a few minutes before they closed and was told we could not get anything as she was still working on drinks.
Lame. Lacking customer service 101👎
Not sure the owner would appreciate this review.

Drip coffee was really bad, some sort of chemical taste. No silverware or plastic ware to eat the other half of my eggs that fell out of my breakfast sandwich. The staff and atmosphere are generally uninviting. Plenty of other coffee shops around to try before this one.

we said dine in but was given to-go cups, felt like they didn’t want us to dine in….they could definitely work on the friendliness of the customer service. my latte came out warm not hot. the coffee was interesting lots of fruity notes, not my favorite. the food was really good though i got a breakfast bagel and a cinnamon roll.
Great food run down no liquor license
Kendra is great server, she is nice, respectful and knowledge of her menu.
Best pizza ever
Kendra is the best. Super nice. Great service!
Great people. Chattanooga legend.

Ordered two large chopped wiener plates and two hotdogs no slaw on 12/21/24. I don't know what happened but the food taste was atrocious. My cousin had the other chopped wiener plate and she mention that hers didn't taste right as well. It was to tangy for some odd reason😖. So, we both stopped eating our food and I called them about 5 ish or so to let them know our concerns. The young lady was pleasant as I described what I was tasting in my food and she said that their sauce does have vinegar in it and I said that's what it could have been to vinegary?🤔 She put me on hold to get a Mgr to speak with me but she wasn't available at that time and she took my name and phone number for the Mgr to give me a call. I put the food in the fridge just in case thay wanted me to bring it back. I patiently waited and by 10 pm I trashed our food and of course no phone call received from them as of 9 am Sunday...... 40.00 in the garbage.

My whole family Looooves MEMOS!!! I can't wait until they open their inside dining room up and start back having live music for customer appreciation! They haven't been a staple in the community for over 50 years for no reason! Great honest respectful family.  The 4 generations of Williams' family are all serious about their customer service skills.  They teach the children from very young ages about how to treat the customers and it shows! They light up whenever they see us coming and even remember our usual order.  The customer service should be studied because they are all naturals! I Would definitely recommend!
One of our favorite spots in Chattanooga. Great food and always the best service.

This past Monday my husband and I celebrated our first year of marriage. We came here the year before during our honeymoon and it was so nice to come back! It's so beautiful in the evening. Nick made it extra special for us, he was so helpful and kind. He recommended a good wine to take home. The mixed drinks don't disappoint, my husband's drink was powerful! If you're going to the Social for the first time, I recommend the pot roast nachos to share and their fried chicken. This is now our anniversary tradition!
Me and my wife came for our first anniversary and couldn’t have been happier. Nick took care of us so well and the drinks and food were amazing. Highly recommend this place to everyone!
Stopped in for a couple of cocktails after a nice long walk - very relaxing.
Fun location, with great service. The cocktails weren't the best, but the food was fantastic.
Great southern classics, all the way down to the cornbread and sweet tea.  Homemade desserts.
I pick up lunch for my boss almost every day.  Love, love the buffet lunch.
Love Southern Star. Always fresh h,  very nice and helpful. Nice hot bar daily. Free desserts on Friday over 25$
Food is consistently good, fresh, and restaurant is clean
