reviews.text: Food was great! Very affordable as well. I'll definitely be back
Very good food and excellent chef! Hidden gem of Chattanooga for halal food lovers. Pizza and wings were amazing!

I’ve been enjoying the delicious food at UPD since 2007, and it never disappoints! Their hummus is hands down the best I’ve ever had—so creamy and flavorful. While I do miss their old gyros and seasoned fries, everything on the menu is still fantastic. The fresh, authentic flavors keep me coming back year after year. If you’re craving authentic Mediterranean cuisine, UPD is a must-try! And the owner is very kind too.
Raised the prices, now charge for tea. Great fried chicken

Server was great, but the food was undeniably mid. Ive never had fried chicken and not finished it until now. Didn’t even taste like they used salt. Some of the sides was good tho. Don’t fully regret going, but i doubt i go back

My family of 6 decided to visit today. The server was excellent, she met every need. My only complaint is the potato in white sauce tasted different, still good but different and the potato salad changed, unless it's not homemade I understand,product comes in different sometimes. I will still be back. Best fried chicken around.
Some of the best southern food you can find.
Giovanni was absolutely awesome when we stopped in on impulse one night. Ben and Jerry's is brilliant as always, and he went out of his way to make sure that we got paired with the perfect flavors.

I mean it’s a cool place with yummy ice cream how can it not get five stars? They must actually really dig in to customer service here, although all the staff has turned out to be very young and likely to be ride in fact they have been outstanding. We go here often because of the products obviously but it makes a lot easier to keep going back because of the staff being kind.
Yummy ice cream. Absolutely disgusting tables, chairs, floor, and bathroom.
Ice cream was good!!! Cone was stale🥹
Such a lovely experience! Kenzie was kind and bubbly, and the ice cream did not disappoint.

I was celebrating a special occasion for my wife, and called ahead and asked them to have champagne in the room. Not only was the champagne in the room but they had chocolate covered strawberries as well. Beautiful property, best hotel for miles in any direction. Would stay again.
Exquisitely beautiful. Has an Old English Manor feel with fantastic attention to every detail . Will definitely go back

The Sewanee Inn is a favorite here on the mountain. On my most recent visit, I stopped by the front desk/concierge with a question and Hayden greeted me with a warm smile. They were very helpful and kind; great hospitality is always appreciated.

The hotel restaurant is great. Food is tasty and decently portioned for the price. The bar's cocktails are well made.

Everything about this Inn was just wonderful!  The staff were attentive and friendly.  The rooms were beautiful!  The restaurant, bar and wedding food was delicious!  We enjoyed the coffee, tea and water station.  I appreciated the lovely fruit creations that changed daily.  The foyer and sitting room were so welcoming, especially with that fire place!  Thank you for making our stay so special.

Visited while doing the TN Whiskey Trail from one side of TN to the other. This is the only one that would not let us participate unless we purchased something first.
We have spent 100s of dollars on multiple bottles as well as other merchandise like t shirts, stickers glasses etc.
There demand lost a sale/s and a customer.
Immediately walked across the street to Chattanooga Whiskey Co. and got a passport stamp and chip and spent near 100 dollars on bottles and merchandise. If they don't want to participate in the whiskey trail they should remove there name from the list.
Been here a few times - fun spot to try out some of their local distills.
I had a wonderful time with the tour guide Briana. She is very knowledgeable and fun.

I have been here so many times and never have I ever had such a horrible experience. I legit waited for 30 mins on drag night for someone to acknowledge me. Josh was busting his butt and in the weeds, the old chick with him was lazy and did nothing. We flagged her down several times and she just stared and moved to the next person.  It has definitely gone downhill since the new people have started. Won’t be back.
The customer service just sucks here. You have to wait a good 15 to 20 minutes to get any kind of help. Good luck to this place.
Very good!
Great food and great service.
This is very nice home-cooked restaurant I thought that you could din in but they told me no carry-out only due to that freaking covid virus
Great food
Great soul food.  Peach cobbler is too sweet.

Best Chocolate in Chattanooga!
Heck this place has chocolate comparable to Switzerland!!

If you want a decadent indulgence, treat yourself to a hot chocolate and slice of cake at the Hot Chocolatiers. Probably the smoothest chocolate ever made. The atmosphere is cozy with lots of natural wood and soft lighting. I purchased a box of 12 truffles for $44 with tip. The truffle assortment appeals to all tastes with mint, whiskey, lemon, salted caramel, pecan, strawberry, and many more fillings. A nice selection of grab and go items too. The only drawback was the parking. I don’t know why Chattanooga is so un-business friendly with its parking, but I wish Hot Chocolatier would open at Gunbarrel or Cambridge Square, where it is easy to access.
Everyone is super friendly and, the Salted Butterscotch hot chocolate is AMAZING!
Parking sucks

They donuts are great but, even getting there at 10, the selection is always heavily limited. I used to love them but now I've been disappointed for the past 5 visits. Now on the lookout for another donut place with his gourmet donuts.

My wife and I love trying local donuts when we travel. This might be the best one yet! I truly regret not leaving with more than one dossant. Their children were awesome donut ambassadors as well. We will definitely stop again next time we are in Chattanooga
Great family owned place!  Donuts are fantastic!!!

Got a 12" take and bake pizza and it was $27.00. That was pretty surprising when I got to the store, but I should have asked when I called in instead of assuming. Also, I had to call in to place a take and bake order. I feel like that should be on their online ordering portal, too.

Followed the instructions to bake their pizza. Exceeded their 12 minute recommendation before moving the pizza off their "baking tray" (large cardboard plate), and the middle of the pizza was still too soft and fell through the oven rack. I'll just get freezer pizza from the grocery store next time.
Great Location + Great Personnel + Terrific Food, best pizza anywhere around + i love their pizza + I keep going back for more!
This has always been our favorite pizza in Chattanooga.

Mean Mug Coffeehouse in Chattanooga is a gem! The atmosphere is warm and inviting, perfect for a cozy coffee date or getting some work done. The food and coffee are absolutely delicious—clearly crafted with care and quality ingredients. Whether you’re a coffee connoisseur or just in the mood for a great bite, this place won’t disappoint. Highly recommend it for anyone in the area looking for a relaxed yet vibrant café experience.

Popped in while getting an oil change and had an amazing chai tea latte. I’m always on the search for the perfect cup and this one was a great mix of slightly sweet but also spicy (cinnamon/chai flavors) with thick and yummy foam. Didn’t get food this time but would highly recommend the chai tea latte!!

Best iced coffee! I wish they had larger sizes.
Their service is always excellent and great attitudes! Thank yall for all you do!

We came here for our 27th anniversary, and it was a great experience. Our server was kind and knowledgeable. The truffle fries were the best I've ever had, even better than Chef Ramsey's, which is high praise from me! I had the fried rice with pork belly, it was good but a little bit too salty for me. My husband had steak frites, he enjoyed it a lot. We had Italian cream cake for dessert, it was delicious.
Great restaurant.  As a local, this is definitely one of the best restaurants in Chattanooga.  I highly recommend Meeting Place.
Great food and atmosphere.

The line is worth the wait! I keep dreaming about the quiche! It was amazing. Also got a chocolate croissant.   Very good. The quality was top notch! I will absolutely 💯 be returning next time I am in town!
My daughter and grandson took me here for breakfast while visiting from out of state.  Very warm and friendly atmosphere.  The food was delightful.  A definite one for the return to list.

The food and drink are both quite incredible and very good value.

The BEC was superb. The bacon was thick cut, crunchy on the outside and chewy on the inside. The bread was very softy and chewy. It was perfectly portioned and wasn't left overly full.

The latte was very tasty and mild. However it should be noted they don't offer low fat milk options. The tea was losse-leaf steeped perfectly. However I wish they would give you a bigger cup!

Parking instead great, but not to difficult to find parking. The restaurant will validate your parking.

This place is very popular. Be prepared to stand outside! This is very important if you can't handle waiting in the cold. However service is decently quick.

I was excited to write this review! The people behind the register were very kind in helping me order. So many fancy words and fresh ingredients on the menu that it was difficult to order, and I loved that experience. You get your bakery item immediately and the coffee is served where you walk up to get it; the food is delivered to you where you sit. There is passion in the work of these employees, even the bakers and cooks in the back. My plate was full of savory eggs, potatoes, cheese, ham all slammed artfully together in a skillet that was stupid hot. I loved it so much even if I burn the heck out of my mouth! The caramel latte was great to enjoy after eating, and the water is this pristine stuff from a tap that you get yourself near the bakery-viewing window. The seating was fairly limited, so get there early because this place is popular! I ended up sitting with some really cool people and they had great conversation. I am full of food now and I am happy. Good post-workout food with high protein! (+1 for the Erlanger discount)

-Blackberry lemon lavender scone 4/5
-Caramel latte 5/5
-Ham and gruyere skillet 5/5 (had some awesome bread to eat with it....once again let that puppy cool down haha)

Decided to come here on Saturday lunchtime. Was not good at all. Ribs were dry and not fresh at all. Macaroni n cheese was watery, not good, sent it back, and got fries. Baked beans were just pork n beans with a little bbq sauce, not good. Green beans were alright. I believe they did not give their best and were caught slacking.  If you gonna claim to be the best, then you need to give your best at ALL times.  Probably would not recommend for the fact that there are so many other good BBQ restaurants in the area.
Great food.

The bake beans seemed old, ribs that are costly were barely warm and didn't seem fresh as well, really dried out and no smoke or much of an flavor. Fried okra and tater tots were great, like made to order. Waitress was very good and friendly. Was expecting better food for the price. Never finished my ribs or beans. Like the beans have been in a crockpot for days.
Not the best BBQ.  Meat very dry and finely chopped.

This is one of my favorite places to go in Chattanooga. His flavors knock it out of the park! Great for a day date or family time. The owner is a hoot and staff is always kind. Keep up the great job River street!
P.S. Get the Elena ruz
Bruce is the best and so are his sandwiches!

Best Deli in the whole state of Tennessee by far. Me and my buddy Steve got to meet Bruce the owner and he gave us all this history behind his deli and gave us some phenomenal recommendations! My buddy had the Cuban sandwich with a chicken tortilla soup on the side and it was fantastic. I got the chopped Italian Hoagie and it was just what I needed this morning. To anyone in Chattanooga looking for a Deli, I would heavily recommend the river street Deli These guys know what they’re doing.
Such great sandwiches! Stopped by while passing through town, perfect lunch spot. People really sweet, laid back vibe.
Staff was super friendly. If I could give more than 5 stars, the food is worth it.

The foods tastes so terrible.
I did not hope it would be as Authentic, but their taste didn't even close to Thai food at all.

The Thai tea was just tasted a bit of tea and watered down.
Tomkha and Tom yum tasted like something artificial to make it sour.

Pad See Ew was so salty.

Duck green curry was tasteless as I assumed they added just a tiny of green curry paste. And they gave us just few small pieces of duck.

For roasted duck, it is very dry and not even hot. The sauce taste is weird also.

I forgot to take pictures because I was in disappointed feeling and I did not think about review at that time.

The waitress that wear glasses is very kind and sweet.
Another lady, she does not have service mind.
Good foods, excellent services,  we will come back again😊😊
Can't comment on the food as we left after sitting for 20 minutes with no service
We left after 21 minutes, we gave up as not even a drinks order was taken, only 4 other tables in the restaurant at 2pm on a Saturday.
Superb.

One of the best tapas restaurants I've been to and I'm from Atlanta, where we have tons of tapas restaurants. The ease of making a reservation and editing the time on OpenTable made things stress free. The ambience and lighting of the restaurant was very romantic. Red wine was perfect. Tapas were a great portion size and very delicious!! Highly recommend the asparagus and patatas bravas!

We have visited this restaurant a handful of times and love it every single time. We are digital nomads and are thinking of moving to the area, but don’t even live here full time. Amada has the perfect blend of flavors, plenty of tapas to make a good meal without feeling stuffed, a beautiful atmosphere, and the sweetest eclectic drinking glasses. Forgot to take photos but don’t let that stop you from trying this place!

Honestly one of the best places I’ve eaten at in the Southeast. We went for our anniversary and enjoyed several cocktails with our tapas. The service was impeccable- our server explained the menu well and was warm, but gave us just the right amount of space to talk and really enjoy our evening (sometimes I feel rushed out of restaurants and this was not the case at Amada!). Truly, everything we tried was so well seasoned, had so much flavor, and had beautiful textures. Reminds me of a meal in a Michelin-star restaurant. Plus, our bill was so reasonable for everything we ate and drank. I was really blown away! I’ve begun recommending this place to all of my friends, even though most of us live over an hour away. Also, parking is pretty easy if you’ve ever parked in a city- find a spot, follow the payment instructions, etc. Highly recommend!!

Service was great. They were very sweet and kind. Food was maybe just not our cup of tea. I ordered the cinnamon swirl french toast and it was extremely dense cuts of loaf bread with little flavor. almost like the consistency of fruit cake…? i was a bit confused. I ate 1 of 3 slices before giving up. Husband had a basic egg & cheese biscuit but it was the oddest biscuit we’ve ever had haha i think we were expecting more of a southern style biscuit and it was far from it.
Definitely for some because the place was very busy but not for us.  However I will reiterate that every employee we encountered was amazing.

I really wanted to like this place but was very underwhelmed. OJ says fresh squeezed but it’s Great Value OJ (you can see it in the fridge). $2.50 to add cheese to my omelette but they didn’t add it and my server was too busy eating her own meal at the bar to check on me at any point after delivering my food (even after she finished eating). Grits were very lumpy and lacked any flavor. I ordered a fruit bowl and the grapes still had little pieces of vine so you can’t eat that with a fork because you have to pick at it. Finally got to the pineapple and it tasted strange, almost like they used a dirty knife or cutting board or maybe it was sitting exposed in a fridge? All that and parking is it free.
I’m only leaving this review so they know what they need to improve upon. I really hope they make the changes needed to succeed. I can’t say I plan on coming back, there’s just too much good brunch competition around here.
Literally the best fried chicken in town.

Food is ok. My issue is with the staff. They are very fire happy. I’ve never worked there , but have heard horror stories of employees who are friends of mine getting fired over simple miscommunication and tiny mistakes. DO BETTER!! would never recommend anyone to work here or even eat here with the overall poor attitudes of management!!!!
Great fried chicken! Fast service.

Wow, what have I been missing! I travel a lot, all over, and can’t recall the last time I had such a pleasant first time experience.

Besides the food being incredible I also spoke to several people who were passionate about the cause.

First time in had amazing food, they let me try and huge chunk of brisket, everything hot season perfectly.

There is no real way to explain it you really need to just visit it and see yourself

Good BBQ, great service and a very pro-American, pro military atmosphere, even if most of the military pics are of this who've died. Lots of parking, lots of seating. Cobbler good; green beans were spicy, brisket also solid. Not sure if I can truly say it better than Edley's or Sugars
This place has earned itself a new lifelong customer! Amazing food, amazing service!

Pizza bros has the best slice in town. Their food is always so fresh and the atmosphere is always great. Service is sometimes hit or miss but for the most part they do a great job. I love their greek salad, spicy cowboy pizza, and their ranch is to die for. I highly recommend!

If you want to listen to an entire taylor swift Playlist while you eat your pizza then this is the place ! 😑👎

Edit : I was in there for over an hour and that's all I heard

I came in with my boyfriend while on a vacation and Gabby was so sweet! I have a ton of food allergies and she was able to answer all of my questions. She was personable and seemed like she really enjoyed her job! It was really nice to go somewhere that had amazing food and also great service. I will be back, and I hope that Gabby is my server again!!
Gabby was a delightful server!

We chose to come here kind of last minute when we found out that the other restaurant we were going to was closed. Wasn't really sure what to expect, but was not disappointed at all. The food was great. I had the chicken alfredo and my partner has the shrimp scampi. The garlic knots are amazing! The drinks were very good also. We loved the performance too. It is a really cool idea to have the servers do the songs and dance. I loved it and will most certainly be back.

An exceptional dining experience
Milli Vanilli meets theatrical performing arts - Good Italian cuisine - Music for the Soul

We really enjoyed the atmosphere and the people. It really is a one-of-a-kind experience. It is very unique and interesting.  All the performers/servers were great! The choice of music was of very popular and well-known artists, and the performers put on a heck of a show!

One thing that stood out was the lackluster food. The bread and salad was the best part of the meal. The chicken marsala was too watery, bland, with no flavor. The noodles were just plain, flavorless noodles.

The atmosphere was unique. The staff were all great.  However,  the food was not good at all.  Very overpriced for what you received!  The vegetables were very salty and the shrimp scampi tasted watery and plain. The drinks were not made well either.

$65 for microwaved pasta meals.  $12 per watered down drink.  Wait staff forced to lip sync to songs on stage.  Not only a prime example of the state of things when as a wait staff you have to perform, but also slows service.  Won’t be back.
Great coffee and great people.

This cozy little coffee shop is a true gem! Their treats are fantastic, and the coffee is always on point. But what really sets this place apart is the staff—they’re incredibly friendly, welcoming, and make every visit feel special. It’s the perfect spot for great food, great coffee, and even better service. Highly recommend!
Cute little coffee shop with a fun and creative seasonal drink menu

I've been wanting to come here for YEARS, but the timing never panned out. However my friend and I finally got the chance to swing by.

I ordered the Iced Lavender Latte with oat milk and my friend got the Iced Peppermint Mocha. I've heard great things about this place, and once I had my first sip of my drink I knew why. My latte was just outstanding. My drink was flowery, it had the perfect amount of lavender syrup. The espresso and oat milk blended together so smoothly, and the sweetness level was exactly how I like my drinks to be. I have no complaints about this drink, it's my standard latte reference now. My only complaint is that I finished this drink too quickly because it was that good.

This place is very cute. The coffee shop is in a small space inside, and there's another space across with more seating. Service was great, they were very friendly. I loved the greenery all around the space and decor. It had such a cool vibe. I love how they redid the space in a historic building. The soft pink theme and lush green plants make a cute combination and overall theme.

I look forward to coming back here again and I'll recommend this place to anyone.

This used to be the best Starbucks downtown and every time I get a drink there now it’s messed up. Also, don’t even waste your time ordering anything with cold foam because they will not blend it long enough. It just feels like things have gotten lazy here in the past 6 months.
Staff is very kind and helpful

Always such a lovely experience with this Starbucks the past years I've lived here. It has the friendliest staff and quick service! Always going out of their way and I loved the note that made my morning when sipping my coffee!
They couldn’t make my drink because they closed in 40 minutes. Absolutely crazy
They were out of chips(after we ordered pimento cheese), out of honey, out of several beers. It took us over an hour to get food and they weren’t busy. The waitress was very rude.
Service was terrible. Was not busy at all. Waitress didn’t bring drinks out for nearly 20 minutes. Out of chips, out of honey. Incredibly slow.
We were in town at a paving expo and had lunch here on day 2 .... lunch was great .... my tea glass never got empty....

Booked online ahead of time and had the Valentines special the day after which included (our choices) 1 appetizer (fried green 🍅🍅), 2 entrees (shrimp & grits, honey dusted fried chicken), & 1 dessert (banana pudding) at a great value. All the food was excellent and our server Maggie was the best. She was so personable and just the right amount of checking in on us.

Casual atmosphere and just the laid back and enjoyable environment we needed. Saw families, couples, groups of teens...all generations. And the food came quickly so we had time before heading to the Imax to walk a bit around Warehouse Row...not enough to offset the caloric intake but...would highly recommend.

The cook must have forgotten to season the chicken in my asheville hot chicken & ranch melt. It’s a nice sandwich but absolutely flavorless besides the pickles. Disappointing because I was passing through town and took my food to eat on the road. The spiced pumpkin bisque was delicious. I had to pay for parking at the Chattanooga location just to pick up my to go order.
Probably the most under appreciated restaurant in Chatt! Great food every time with GF pad Thai that my celiac boys love!
I have been here twice. Both times the customer service was good and the food was quite tasty.

Rude waiter..... usually I will tip very well today I didn't. The waiter was rude and when I told him that my fish was wrong argued with me.... I have IBS so eating can be challenging at many places but when you argue about chicken being pork and my boyfriend is a farmer and confirmed it was chicken then you no longer deserve a tip plus he came by the table three times once to seat us and take our order one refill of tea then to drop off the check... My boyfriend and Son got sick immediately after eating here. We won't be back again we frequent many Thai restaurants but this was the worst I've ever been to with so many better Thai restaurants choose some places else if you have any dietary restrictions please avoid because if they are going to serve whatever they want it's not safe here if you have food allergies
Delicious ice cream!  Worth the trip!  🙌🏻🤤
Such a great little spot for ice cream! The shop has a fun vibe, and the ice cream was delicious. Perfect place to stop and treat yourself. Definitely worth a visit!
It was good ice cream and worth the stop, but nothing special.

I have a soft spot in my heart for Clumpies and I think their ice cream is one of the better places in town. However, you should be aware that some flavors are hit or miss. I love love loved the lemon ice box but found firecracker to be disgusting. I think it’s great that they have so many different flavors to choose from, and that they’re always changing.
Delicious cupcakes and cookies. Great variety with really different flavors. Cookies alike. Very warm, friendly and attentive service. They make you want to come back.
The sugar free brownie is so good! Great customer service!

Such a super cute place! They have so many wonderful desserts, and everything is beautifully displayed. The cupcakes were absolutely delicious—moist, flavorful, and perfectly frosted. A must-visit for anyone with a sweet tooth!

Lots of options. It was hard to choose but I got the Almond Raspberry.  It was DELICIOUS.  They mostly have cupcakes but have other options as well like cookies, macaroons and a few other things.  My cupcake was a little over $5 with tax.  The girl that was working was able to explain any cupcake flavor I asked about.  I would visit again.

I hired Cupcake Kitchen for my wedding and that was the best decision I ever made. I still have guest raving about the cupcakes. They were both beautiful and delicious! I was also grateful for their selection of gluten free cupcakes since we had some guest with dietary restrictions.
10/10 EVERY.SINGLE.TIME!
Best mocha and muffins

The food here is great.  You walk in and order and pay at the counter before finding your own seat with a number.  You are also asked to tip when you pay.  I'm not a fan of tipping before service.  Speaking of the service, which is really lacking, we had to get our own refills on coffee and napkins and whatever else we needed.   The wrong food was brought to the table, and when they did figure out what we ordered, it was all brought out at different times.

The food and service are always great here. I love Five Guys, despite its prices. But the main reason I write is out of a concern for the safety of customers and staff.

At least the last 4-5 times I have been to the Broad St. location, there has been at least one homeless person hanging out somewhere in the store. Usually the worst that happens is they ask for your leftovers, but the last time, a man was sitting at the closest table to the door with his belongings strewn all over the table, including an open sleeping bag which I had to step around on my way out of the store. He immediately got up from the table and got behind us in line and then for whatever he ordered, if he actuallyordered anything. I was with my daughter, and we had planned to eat there, but this guy made her so uncomfortable she preferred to take ieat at home.

And the whole reason I stood waiting for the food in the waiting area instead of at a table that last time I was there (within the last couple weeks) was because the time I was there before that, a man who was in line in front of us when we arrived got out of line while pretending to take a call, fiddled with the peanuts behind us while we ordered, and stole our food when it got called while I was in the restroom.

The kind staff immediately re-made the order for me to their credit, and it is always service with a smile from them. I write this though in part out of concern for them, however, as while there are 4-6 people usally on shift, most if not all of them lately have been rather small women who would have trouble subduing an adult male threat if one of these characters ever decided to be even more aggressive.

Needless to say I won't bring my daughter into this store again.
Slow to acknowledge I was even there and then took them longer than expected to finish the order

We love this place
A fun outing
Great view
Always fast. Always good
Employees are extremely rude. Most definitely will NOT be back! Not to mention I asked for a combo and was charged 6$ extra due to it being entered in individually. Flat out ridiculous.

The girl that was ready to leave was so rude.  FYI don't ask to try the pickles or have them on the side. It is not allowed. And don't ask for extra pickles for your $15 combo. It is toooo hard and they give you 3! Lol not again
Can’t rate atmosphere because I did drive through.  Food is great and fast!  Love me some Jimmy John’s!!
Driver never showed up over an hour, driver said she called. I work security sat out front of building waiting for driver to never show.
Tremendous store. Very entertaining. Even if you don't want to shop, I recommend visiting it. This is the story of the most famous candy in the city.
Different flavored moon pies big and small and other snacks God bless the ladies for allowing us to browse and purchase in the store after closing mix and match small dozen for $5 was great
Super helpful staff, great selection
Drink wasn’t on par and Birch did me a solid and exchanged the drink and it was great. With awesome service like his, this place should be always one to come and visit at Rock City.

This location is one of the roomier Starbucks I've been to.  Sitting area is reminiscent of the local cosy coffee shop.  A little alcove is perfect for study group and there's a larger table great for collaborative workspace.  Nice fireplace provides an intimate feel in the larger space.  Overall it's a well appointed space. Coffee order was on point.

I had a great experience at this location.  I was served by a wonderful individual and my food was out in no time!  The food was delicious, I got the grilled cheese on sour dough and it was amazing!! My chai tea was also on point, I highly recommend stopping in if you’re up seeing rock city and want a refreshment or a quick bite before or after going in.
Beautiful views, knowledgeable/helpful/attentive wait staff. Food was delicious and appetizing..
Food was okay. The atmosphere, views out on the deck are amazing! Nice pool

Thank You Debbie and Lamar for taking such good care of us!
We loved our dinner and football game watching at the bar!
You made our whole evening an incredible experience

We had dinner here our first night of our stay. Our server Costace was very friendly and made some great recommendations on the crab hush puppies and bread pudding dessert. The bartender Debbie made me an amazing eggnog martini. Overall it exceeded our expectations!

I ordered a take out dinner for 8:15pm on 02/14/25 - rib eye steak cooked medium rare with a side of broccoli and a garden salad from the Chattanooga, TN Longhorn. I showed up to Longhorn at 8:13pm, pulled into a ToGo parking spot, and checked in using the text they sent me at 8:08pm. After waiting for over 15 minutes, I finally got out of my car and went into the restaurant to pick up my food. Sure enough, my meal was just sitting at the bar, bagged up and ready to go, but forgotten by the servers.  I walked out with my food at 8:34pm, 21 minutes after arriving. Unfortunately, I had already included a tip in the amount I paid - I will not make that mistake again.

When I got home and began to eat, I found my steak was cooked maybe medium well, more likely well done. It was the toughest and dryest rib eye steak I’ve ever had the misfortune of eating. The salad and broccoli were fine - no complaints there. But overall, the “star” of the show was disgusting. I literally fed half of it to my dog because I didn’t want any left overs. Fortunately, there is a Texas Roadhouse and an Outback within 5 minutes of Longhorn - guess I’ll be going there next time.
Great service. Relaxing atmosphere.
All around great food
Food and service has always been great here.

I have been here on more than one occasion hoping they will get better. Do not get lunch here unless you have an hour + to wait on your food. This is likely the worst managed lunch option in downtown Chattanooga.
Very quality food, staff did their job, and the place I found peaceful. Thanks again Panera!
I pick up bagels and pastries to go for the office. And surprisingly cheaper than Munchkins.

I’ve always enjoyed myself here until one night a few of the male security guards literally bombarded the girls restrooms while me & my friend were trying to use the restroom. I was completely thrown off by their behavior as they were yelling at us to leave bc they were closing. I was very frustrated and gave them the same energy. I decided to pull my phone out & record the incident, but due to retaliating..I was banned lol I’m not even mad about it, just wanted to share my experience. I wish there was a 0 star rating bc they clearly don’t care how they treat paying customers.
Always such a fun and safe environment!!!
loveeeee blacking out here 🩷🩷🩷 so much fun with friends (from what i remember lol)
Great vibes and amazing staff!!!

I loved this cozy place to eat and enjoy time with those in life. The decor provides a relaxing environment to eat delicious crepes loaded with sweet or savory fillings; and yes, even both can be enjoyed side by side. They offer so much more, sandwiches, potatoes, salad. My omelette was large and so tasty: filled with fresh veggies. I just wanted more of those delicious potatoes. I can’t forget the gluten free crepe batter.

Original Review:
Nice atmosphere, modern look. However, the biggest problem is the food: the crepes are bland and doughy with color only on a single side with every other part tasting and feeling more like a ravioli. The sauces are too concentrated and overused (likely to cover up the crepe itself) overpowering the ingredients used inside. The savory crepe ingredients taste as if they forgot to open the spice cabinet.

Would not return as it isn't worth the cost, especially when you don't even get a full glass of lemonade when you order it
Love ambiance and food is delicious 😋
Fantastic menu and staff! Everything was delicious the ribeye for two with their fries was a great main course. Dry aged ribeye and the crispiest fries ive ever had. Drinks were phenomenal also!

My friend and I were staying at the hotel and tried out the Auld Alliance this past weekend. The manager was very friendly and answered all our questions about the restaurant before we made a reservation. Our server, Loki, was excellent and very knowledgeable. The food was fantastic! We loved everything we got. We will definitely come again.
Beautiful location, excellent wait staff (THANK YOU, Loki), phenomenal food.
The most delicious meal in Georgia. Beautiful, delicious food, great service. Thank you Niko for your exception service this evening. We will definitely be back
Service was great. The eggs and beet juice were amazing. The breakfast was great.
We stopped here by chance on the way to Chattanooga airport.  Our server "Mo" was friendly and efficient-  food was very good and priced reasonably.
Excellent food and service!  Mo was a wonderful server!

I stayed in the Kinley Hotel and ate at The Exchange after checking out on a Sunday morning.  As a local, shame on me for not trying this place sooner. The menu has great options, the coffee is local, the food is delicious and the service was fantastic (shout out to Mo).

They serve brunch 7am to 3pm, seven days a week. I will be back!
Olivia makes an amazing Negroni!  This place is super chill and hip with high end offerings.
tables not cleaned off. service slow. half and half for coffee tasted old.
Food had a good taste. Sandwich didn't look like the picture.  And was overpriced for what we got.
Very clean, helpful staff and I LOVE the chicken and rice soup.
Great workers, awesome service
What can I say, never bad at panera

Got one of the new Asiago bagel stacks, the Chicken Roma one, I did not customize it at all. I got it with everything on it. When I received the sandwich, barely had any basil, no arugula, Garlic aoli, or green dressing. Very disappointing.. and on my birthday none the less.
Great place always yummy.

Awful. Just awful. Imagine this - you order Panera for delivery. You put in the specifics and the restaurant still manages to get it wrong. I asked for Parmesan cheese in the French onion soup - got none. Got a small tiny plastic box with less than a handful of lettuce but covered in cheese and the wrong dressing. Now normally, this would be just an inconvenience. For me, it is not. I’m paying for the delivery because I cannot drive - I am disabled. You guys for some reason only use uber eats which is another awful company. So since your restaurant was closed by the time I got my food I couldn’t even pay MORE money and uber there and back to get WHAT I ORDERED. And to top it off, uber eats thinks the photos I sent are correct?! Caesar salad dressing ISNT GREEN OLIVE OIL!!!!!!!! I will never ever make the mistake of ordering food from Panera ever again. For more information and details regarding this store location and order details, message me.

The food is always good.   We had an issue with the order ahead, though. We ordered on the app, and they kept pushing order order back. It wasn't ready when it said it would be. Finally, my wife went up to the counter and said something, and they said it just came in even though it had been on the board for some time.  After that, they finally got it out.

The people that work here are super slow, unless you have 20 minutes to wait for 2 sandwiches I’d go somewhere else. Lots of standing around and moving really really slow, talking and looking half asleep while making food. The guy with the nose piercing was not friendly, I asked for a box for my sandwich and he wouldn’t give me one. Solid pass, it’s really nasty inside
This Panera has the slowest drive thru I have ever experienced. It always takes forever. I miss Eiesteins bagels.

I decided to dine in, the ambiance was excellent and calling to me to sit and stay for awhile,  which I promptly did. I was taken back by the chatty employees who were a breath of fresh air. We only talked about the foods they serve and all the lovely fresh baked breads! Lovely atmosphere, lovely people. My kinda place. It was relaxing. I'll say it again, it was relaxing
No sense in being a sips member here. Drive thru is never open in the mornings.

This Panera is one of the nicest locations within the Chattanooga area. Very well designed and usually fairly clean. There does always seem to be a staffing issue with this store so product can be slow to come out and the coffee dispensers are empty more times than not, so don't be in a hurry to grab something quick and get out. The food quality has always been good anytime we've ordered here. If the company would police their products, check stock, and check the dining area more often, it could easily be a near perfect Panera. But as it sets, it's a 3.5 on a normal day up to a 4 star place when they're cooking.

The microwave in which I was to heat up my own sweet roll was dirty inside as well as outside.
The cashier was friendly and helpful, tho.

Some girl body checked me at the bar so I went to security instead of handling it. They ended up kicking me out for “causing problems” after telling me to stay outside while it’s freezing to avoid her and then said I was staring her down even tho I was outside aka while nothing happened to her yet I got kicked out. Used to love that place. No longer feel safe there
Had a blast on the fly
Love this place!
Kids bar. The ice smelled and tasted like the worst toilet water.
Annabelle was the extreme wonderful server who was able to help with everything I needed. Chelsea was a very experienced bartender. Nolan did excellent security.

Don’t miss this relaxing place if u are in the region, especially BoomBox drink

What a hidden Jim and Chattanooga at the top of the aloft apartment next to Hamilton Place mall near Carrabba’s is a quaint and relaxing bar up on the seventh floor. Highly recommended. They have pool tables seats all over and it’s just a good place to hang out and chill.
The prime rib was excellent, the drinks were good not great. Sat at the bar, service was good.

Excellent food, drinks, and service. What I don't understand is the lighting choice for dinner. It is blindingly bright. It catches you off guard, so I'd ask to either sit at the bar or on the patio, not near the kitchen. I'm really curious as to why it's so bright during dinner. After dinner, we went next door to what I believe is their sister establishment, Nightcap. It was lovely. Highly recommend checking it out.
Exceptional experience. Phenomenal food. Bartender set the tone!!!! Overall remarkable experience.
We always enjoy a fantastic meal and outstanding service at Gillman Grill, a favorite gathering spot for family and friends in Chattanooga!

First of all, I would like to thank all the staff of Whitebird for the magical night for dinner.
This restaurant is on the first floor of the Edwin Hotel right next to the Walnut Street bridge, Hunter Museum, and all the romantic spots in the art district.

With this type of setting, you know the night will be magical. Extra points for whoever came up with the idea to out see through igloo"s just outside the restaurant patio next to the bridges. Yes, you are reading that correctly. You can spend a romantic dinner in a see-through igloo with white lights and all the night sky in an intimate, darker setting.  You only find two of these, so i would book in advance for this special venue.
My date and I absolutely loved the decor, atmosphere, staff, and the food.

I have a gluten allergy to Wheat, and all the staff went out of their way to make sure my night was perfect with no cross-contamination.

The owner, manager, and all the staff were top-notch for a true white glove fine dining should be.

Now to the food. I ordered the salad, thinking it would be on the smaller side.  Nope, it was a large portion and amazing flavor with ingredients not used much in salads you would find at a restaurant. This was a real chef cooked/ prepared to order.
Next, we had the grilled chicken mini sliders with a sauce that was delicious to dip into. I'm not sure what it was, but wow, it made the flavors come out more.
I also got the garlic mashed potatoes. This was definitely my favorite with just the right amount of ingredients and fresh potatoes, not instant garage, like some restaurants try to pass as mashed potatoes. Nope, nothing but the best and finest quality of food, cooked to order Cordon Bleu chef.
They had a gluten free buns, so I got a grilled chicken sandwich that was delicious.

The evening was nothing less but magical with the sunset going down the stung lights in the igloo. Dinner was just perfect and a nice walk on the bridges to in the evening.

I would highly recommend this restaurant and experience for your next romantic dinner date.

Don't take my word for it make. Go see for yourself the magic that awaits.

Would I recommend this restaurant?  Absolutely
Would I return?  Absolutely

We so enjoyed our dinner at Whitebird!! Kenny, our waiter, was so just kind and wonderful. And the food and drinks were amazing!! This is our first visit to Chattanooga, and definitely will return to this restaurant! Beautiful setting, and our 2.5 year old ate more than she ever has while eating out! I couldn’t have been happier.

The filet was AMAZING! My husband loved the Harvest Salad with chicken.

Everyone was so kind. Thank you, all!

This was our first visit to Chattanooga. We enjoyed the food and atmosphere of the Whitebird. However, we did buy a bottle of wine with the understanding that we could recork the bottle and take it home. At the meals end, the bar tender started to poor us more wine. I told him not too, but he did anyway, exclaiming “ you can drink the rest”. Well, we had a show to go to and left two full glasses of wine at the table. What a waste and disappointment.

10/10 dining experience! We ordered the biscuits appetizer and these were seriously the best biscuits either of us had ever had. Incredible butter, 2 different kinds of jelly, and an apple butter. Then for dinner I ordered the duck "whitebird" meal in hopes of something I had never had before - the unique vegetable hash was hearty and delicious (even dabbled with the extra apple butter to add some sweetness with great success) and the duck was very palatable. Very wonderful dinner. My girlfriend ordered the pork belly small dinner plate and was very surprised to love what she ordered. Our waitress was incredibly positive, detailed, came to the table at the right moments, gave positive insight into dishes we had questions about, and kept our drinks full. Other staff came by the table smiling but not intrusively which we thought was very welcoming. Also, big props to the hostess (I believe her name was Reagan?) for securing us our table on Valentine's Day evening when we needed to change our time to later in the evening. The atmosphere was warm and modern without over-sophistication. Loved that we could see the kitchen staff working methodically in the back. After the experience with the biscuit appetizer we're thrilled to try brunch one day! We will be back!
Great food and atmosphere. I highly recommend the Whitebird Martini and the chicken pot pie!

Great experience dining here. The food is excellent and very well priced. There a lot of different flavors to explore through their dishes.

They also have half off oysters during happy hour. They have a large variety which were all delicious.

The tasting menu was a very great way to sample a lot of the items. It was very filled.

They also have an excellent tea menu as well as coffee.

I personally found their mock tails to be egregiously overpriced. It's about $8 for what seemed to be about 4 oz. I would not recommend the mock tails.

One of the most beautiful restaurants and experiences we have had in a very long time! Highly recommend for any occasion and outing. The food , drinks and service are impeccable. Our server was knowledgeable and the perfect host. We started with a Zinfandel and nonalcolic chuck taylor that was delicious. Followed by a seaweed and mushroom broth that we could have had more servings of. We went on to a radicchio salad and Rabbitt that was the perfect starter. Next time we will try the mussels! Everything sounds so good. Dinner was the blue crab fusilli and the truffle macaroni and the pasta is delicious! House made with the best sauces. Dessert was the sesame panna cotta and if you go seafood all night I highly recommend this to end the night with. We also the profiteroles with coffee icecream and can easily say this a crowd favourite and something we will dream about forever . We can’t wait to go back

Excellent environment (in winter it is better to prefer a table inside the restaurant rather than on the patio; although it is closed by heavy curtains and heated, it allows some air to pass in from the outside, especially at the last tables in the corner).
Excellent food which is of high quality.
Professional, friendly and helpful staff.
Atmosphere is fantastic, nice open design wonderful decor. Drinks are great and service was excellent.

The atmosphere is nice but the food is over-priced. It's $14 for 6 mediocre wings. The port doesn't count towards the happy hour even though it's listed under wine. Maybe we should have known? It's not clearly communicated on the menu, though. The port was $18 each. In total, the bill was over $50, not including tip, for 6 wings and 2 ports.
Y’all! I don’t even think I could’ve made this sandwich this fast Cory ROCKS!

We had lunch over the weekend and had one of the best Reuben sandwiches I think I’ve had in a very long time..highly recommend River Drifters and we were taken care of by Hannah… Just incredible service thank you for making our lunch a wonderful experience. I will definitely bring more people back next time for lunch and ask for Hannah❤️
I told Ced the cook to make me whatever. 10/10 burger!!!
My wife and I came in from dinner. Megan was amazing! She made us feel so welcome. We will definitely be back

The food was absolutely trash. I ordered the money burger the buns were burnt and the meat as well burnt. The burger was incredibly  dry. The price is 20 for the burger even if it was 15 would still be over priced. I would rate the burger a 5 out of 10 and that's a lot. I compared this burger to the one at Blue Moose there's a huge difference the one at Blue Moose is juicy and well done very savory and cheesy also way cheaper. Save your self the time and go to a different restaurant. The service was great though
Started the weekend off with a great breakfast. A Brunch burrito and French toast with a Monty Palmer
Every time we’ve been here it’s been fantastic.  Hello Monty is the type of place you can’t wait to bring others to visit.

I came to try this place after doing a long hike and it was the best decision I’ve made. Foster was my waiter and he was very attentive and went above and beyond to provide me de best experience as a solo customer.
I juts wanted a burger and french fries and he recommended to add cheese and a fired egg and oh my🙌
Also the beers, he kindly gave me a taste of 2 lager so I could choose the one I liked the best! The whole experience, even as simple as it was, really made my day. I really recommend this place if you come and visit Chattanooga. I’ve stay outside as r was a beautiful sunny day and that added extra points into my experience.
This place is great. Thoughtful plates and excellent service. Taylor! And her collegues.
Super nice people. Great food and the outdoor seating is super cute.

We love this place! We’ve been a few times now and the food is great and the service is even better. Melinda served us this last time and she does a great job at making a connection with the guests. Can’t wait to come back!

Melinda is amazing, greeted everyone, and followed up with each customer by name to ensure they were doing good or if they needed anything. The burgers were good and tasty, just smaller than the last time we stopped in. The fried pickles had too much breading on them, and we could hardly taste the pickles. We enjoy outdoor seating, especially on cooler sunny days, but this particular day another couple had their 2 dogs off leash that kept coming over to us in line and at our table jumping up on us and begging for food. I know the dogs are not the responsibility of the Café but it did take away from our Sunday lunch having to deal with someone else dogs. We will come and do recommend to others to stop by

I was very disappointed with today’s first time experience attempting to dine in at Apricot’s today (9/1/2024). If you are not part of the river community, BEWARE!!! I am a local resident here in this county and I was not acknowledged or helped today.

I was the third customer in line to order my food when a female guide decided to slip right in front of me to order. I didn’t say anything and decided to give her some grace, assuming that she was on a tight timeline to get to another river run. Several other guides then walked around from the side of the building and decided to all cut in front of me by pretending that the girl was saving their place in line. They all knew I was standing right there and they played the ‘let’s not give the eye contact game’. What made me even more upset was that they ended up ordering food for several other people! The lady at the register witnessed all of this go down and when it was finally my turn to order, she ended up closing the window screen on me and told me that she needed time to put the previous orders together before helping me. I have never felt this type of discrimination before in my life. I totally get that the local businesses here in Ocoee depend on river tourism. Don’t forget! Your intended customer base is only seasonal. Us locals give y’all business year round, especially during the slow down months. Do better.

We went for an early dinner and it wasn't busy. The bartender was super sweet and makes delicious drinks. The food was great. Our waitress, Donna was kind,  knowledgeable about the menu and was on point with the service. We will be back! The Espresso Martini was a 10 out of 10.
We had dinner  for four on Christmas Eve. It was very pleasant and relaxing. I would highly recommended.

I had a very pleasant experience here! The staff were friendly and welcoming, the food was delicious (highly recommend the focaccia appetizer), and the atmosphere was elegant, peaceful, and comfortable. Pictures are of the gnocchi and shrimp entrees.

Some of the best southern breakfast food you can find. The fact that most of it is gluten-free is still hard for me to believe. Pure wizardry. It can definitely get a little pricey if you are trying to scratch all your soul food itches at once, but it is always worth the trip.

The people and food here were amazing!! They will treat you like family.  I have celiacs and they were very knowledgeable and accommodating.  Everything was gluten free except biscuits and tortillas!  The baked goods were delicious.  Highly recommend this place!!   It did not disappoint

We were visiting from Huntsville and had the best experience! Our 5 year old is Celiac and it’s so hard to eat out. Bantam and Biddie made it worry free and our son made the claim that the chicken fingers were #1! He also enjoyed the gluten free brownie that was the size of his head. Everyone was friendly and so personable. We will make the drive back to eat again!
Great service, fresh eats, large portions (for the entrees) ands great family atmosphere. Would definitely recommend 👍👍

Amazing GF and other allergen friendly options. Service was incredible, staff is friendly and knowledgeable and passionate about what they do. The food is all made from scratch and tastes very high quality. First time having gluten free chicken & waffles and was not disappointed!!!
$7 for a small kinda expensive, no mil discount, no bathroom, no seating.

Mad Priest creates the best coffee in town.
Once you try it, you will want some more.

This is why we pass on Starbucks and Dunkin every time. Finding places like this and buying a coffee and a bag of beans actually changes the world for good. The flavor is amazing. So your world is better. The servers were friendly and talented coffee folks. Now their world is better. No CEO of a company far far away is getting fatter off this 20 spot. This is local people making a difference for good. Amazing. Thank you.

I was in town for a day and took my pup here. I read reviews ahead and knew to bring my pup’s vaccination records. Easy check-in and a
fun place to hang out. Staff and guests were very friendly. Would definitely go back.

We both absolutely LOVE coming and hanging out here. When we lived close by we were here almost everyday. Staff is friendly and personable, environment is fun for both the dog and myself. It’s a great spot to meet people as well. Will always recommend this spot. In the winter they have plenty of heaters to stay warm and in the summer they have fans and misters to keep cool.
Dogs and beer, what else do you need?
This place was the best. We stopped in on our way through town and everyone was so friendly, the park was so well run. We wish we didn't live halfway across the country!

This place is in serious need of renovation. The second floor is very dirty, and the furniture (especially the sofas) is extremely old and broken. I understand they are trying to create a unique vibe, but for a coffee shop in Northshore, this is unexpected. The drinks are okay, I didn’t try the food. Expect to see many homeless individuals inside.
I love that girl with the bangs - forever the best one
Got the Turtle Coffee and Breakfast Burrito w/sausage. Coffee was not too sweet and well balanced and the burrito was perfect for the cost.
Had a Miss Piggy and a Scorch Orange.  Both were very tasty.  Ambience and service were top notch.

Great service from the  staff from.the time we walked in until we left. Very helpful getting us set up for our first sim experience.

Had fun playing the mini games with our daughter and doing the long drive. Great way to scratch the itch when you need to swing your sticks and cant get to the course.

Food and beer selection was good as well.  Will def go back.

Got fitted for PXG Irons there. Beats going to Atlanta, Knoxville or Nashville.
Bar food drinks and indoor golf simulators.

Doesn’t look like much, but the salads and sandwich had so much flavor—truly delicious! Gluten free bread available without an upcharge!
These ladies are THE BEST as well as the food.

There isn’t a better breakfast joint ANYWHERE. Destiny took incredible care of us. Sweet, attentive and very knowledgeable. She is on her game.

Every. Single. Every time we come to a BBB it is Tier I service, food and atmosphere. Chef Currence is a legend for a reason.

Chicken & Waffles for Wifey & The Demon CHX sando for me. Tier I quality.
I rarely give 5 stars! Fire breakfast!
Clean, friendly, and fast service. Food was awesome!
Service was great food so good. Never had a cornbread omelet before. Destiny was our server and was very nice, and I asked the name of the chef I believe Crystal to, great job.

Whether I'm stopping in for a sandwich or running in to grab quick ingredients, this place is the epitome of what local business should be. Incredible selection, even better people.
The BEST sandwiches in Chattanooga!! Nice atmosphere and people too.
Waitresses and managers are very kind, down to earth, and hospitable. Ribeye and salad was very good! Karaoke was above entertaining. A large longtime staple in Chattanooga. Nice outside area.
Mark Stoker and Badger arel No Limit  Chattanooga Team.  Happy to be back at buds

There is karaoke on the week nights, bands on the weekends and darts. The food is surprisingly very good. The hamburgers are great, the prime rib sandwich and ribeye steaks are fabulous! The salad with sirloin steak is great, the grouper is very good. I have never been disappointed with my meal there.
If your use to chain restaurants (scooters, Starbucks, etc) for coffee I wouldn’t recommend this. Very small portion for the price and very odd flavor
Great Coffee and Merch! Plenty of Space and always featuring different Roasters/Coffee Companies. So go often and feel free to impulse buy one of the adorable mugs like me 😆
Great latte and coffee. Loved the music, space to study and comfortable seating. The views and huge windows give a great view of Lookout Mountain too
Great tasting cortado.

What a find in Ringgold, GA! Blueberry scone warm didn't last long. Yummy! I got a Dirty Chai w/1 shot of expression. My husband got a Cappuccino - large came w/4 shots expression. I see why they have won First Place in the Best of the Best 5 times. Don't miss this gem.

I can't say enough about there coffee and tea drinks, as well as their service and friendliness. This is my family's favorite coffee spots. Please try an orange scone. They're absolutely delicious.

Local bands and friendly staff.
best venue and bar in Chattanooga! say hey to Marty!

Highly recommend!

Owner is so nice and helpful. Incredible selection of Olive oils and balsamic vinegar. You are able to sample all of the flavors. Highly recommend you give them a visit.

My sister and I shared an affogato, which he divided into 2 dishes for us, and it was absolutely delicious.  We will definitely come back often.  There are lots of nice things available to buy as gifts.

Great food.

Best smoothies and smoothie bowls in town. I also love the burrito. For me at least, they strike the perfect balance between health food and taste. I always feel great after a meal and it's always delicious.

Great atmosphere and a solid patio for when it's nice outside. Extremely clean, very friendly staff.  Also, low-key, a fantastic bathroom that feels like a sanctuary.

Great little vegan spot. Good food. A little slow because everything is made to order, so don’t plan on being in a rush.

Leaving 5 stars because I want this place to succeed. I would love to see more vegan and health centered spots do well in chattanooga. My constructive criticism is the entrees weren't great. Burrito and Buddha bowl specifically seemed to lack substance and heartiness and cohesion. Good luck.

as a planner, Sierra is one of my go to gals for wedding cakes and desserts. I know she will deliver beautiful and tasty treats, all while being easy and fun to work with!

I cannot say enough about this dynamic duo.This is where you get the cake to celebrate the most festive moments of your life🤎💚🤍 They squeezed in my order on a busy weekend and  created exactly what I had in mind. Everyone wss blown away by the cake, however, noone was interested in cake after eating so much candy!😂 but the flavor was intoxicatng to say the least. The lemon blueberry blew us away🫨😲🤤 ( the 4 people who ate it 😁)  It was VERY rich and decadent, EVERYTHING that a custom, made to ordercake should be and more. These ladies don't play when it comes to flavor. So thankful that I now know where to get a cake that my guest won't soon. Forget.

Sierra created a beautiful and very delicious cake for our wedding. She was extremely kind and easy to work with, and the quality of her work is just incredible. We thoroughly enjoyed getting to taste the flavors, and our final decision (earl gray) was a huge hit!

Highly recommend Reignbow Baking! I reached out to Sierra about designing a special cake for my MIL's 70th bday. I shared some ideas and photos of what I was envisioning and Sierra brought it to life and beyond! My MIL was so surprised it made her cry and everyone enjoyed the cake - super moist, delicious and decadent. Could not have asked for more!

All the samples we tried were excellent.  My daughter decided on the carrot cake and Dirty Chai for the Bridal Cake layers and the Mexican Chocolate for the grooms cake.  All were exceptional! We received so many compliments.  Sierra even brought unfrosted samples for my mother in law who has a dairy allergy so she could enjoy the cakes as well!  100% recommend

Came here once for coffee and they messed up my order with dairy milk instead of almond milk. Upset my stomach so bad that I was scared to come back. Decided to give them another try and got the matcha this time and it was delicious 10/10!
Cute coffee shop, coffee is mediocre, and it was $14 for lattes which seemed a bit steep.

I was the kid on wensday or thrusday that they gave me a test drink for a Valentine Smoothie, and it was amazing I loved the sweetness of it and the overall taste. So thank you for the test drink and I think it will be a good seller.
Great coffee and a nice place to stay for awhile.
For a single level facility with a giant board with chess pieces. Putt-Putt and other things to do and a manager gave Us coupons for future visits
I do love the wings here.
I had fun, but I just wish their heated bays were a little more warm.

Good coffee. Nice place to hang out.
This is the place to buy coffee beans to give as gifts.

Updating this review since they've moved into the new cafe space. While the old space had the best neighborhood coffee bar vibes, the new space is truly beautiful and worth a visit just for the ambiance, while the staff still provide the cozy friendly vibe you're looking for.
The Owner will not handle incorrect situations with out of control customers properly.
Coziest, comfiest coffee shop in town! The new seasonal matche is my favorite!

The staff was very friendly and did an awesome job. The bread and butter Focaccia bread was amazing, it came with chive oil that was delicious. Wood fire oven pizzas are some of the best in town, give them a try. Pictured: Fresh Mozarella add oregano
My wife and I enjoy our dinner here. Stuffed peppers and the wing plate. The food and service was top notch given how busy they were.
Had the surf and turf. Was very good! Overall great experience here.

First time trying this place and it did not disappointed. We started at the bar asking a Campari and fernet on the rocks and we ended up staying there for dinner. Cocktails were spot on. Good vibe, friendly staff and exquisite menu.
We ordered the spicy Lamb rigatoni and the mozzarella and basil pizza. Everything was delicious.
Always a pleasant experience. Food and service is exceptional.
Sorry guys, got to high for me

Burgers very fresh.  Many choices of condiments including grilled onions grilled mushrooms and green peppers.  If they dont give you enough fries ask for more.  A $6 medium fries usually is plenty for 2 people.

I do not like to disparage anyone unless it is warranted and I believe some is in order due to my recent order.

Let me start by saying the customer service is excellent! Friendly and attentive is all I ask for so that I know my food is being handled with love. So kudos for that at this location across the board.

However I found a very tiny, thick hair in my burger last night and was disappointed but not surprised. I think the few times I have walked in I have noticed that people with beards or mustaches have not been wearing any facial covering at all which i’m sure is definitely required when preparing food.

All I ask is you guys receive this feedback with sincerity and not as a simple diss. I love the quality and taste yall bring in a difficult industry as someone who has been through it but I think the standards just need a slight nudge to ensure quality is upheld.

To the workers yall are excellent, but simply ask yourself if you would want to find someone else’s hair in your food. It’s extremely important to keeping reputation which ensures your livelihood with a job.

I know the pay is probably not what you’d want, but coming from another struggling minimum wage worker I simply want quality and safety when paying a lot more for my food and to not feel like my money isn’t going where I want it to getting a Micky D’s level of care.

Beside this issue, you guys are fantastic cooks and get it done and always LOVE the overwhelming amount of fries! Anyone saying yall don’t make quality burgers don’t know jack about a good burger!

Just please make sure you guys follow standard procedures like clean working stations, interchanging gloves regularly, and wearing beard covers properly! That’s all I ask and I know the good stuff will come my way every time.
Burgers are better than most fast food .

Great food.  We went for breakfast as a group and had a good experience.  Service was slower than expected, but it was early.
Waited 45 mins for our food. The food was not good at all. Also, there are tons of knats and fruit flies all around the tables.  Disappointed. Waste of money. Do better.

Best coffee shop in town. Been a customer for 8 years and it wasn’t until Cadence that I realized how poor Starbucks is. Friendliest staff and great food too. Their banana bread is fantastic. Nothing beats their cold brew though.
Really great coffee and also LOTS of space to work/study/meet with people. You can even rent out their space for gatherings/parties. They have coffee, pastries, and even some food items! Great spot!
Some of the best coffee I have ever had!
absolute best coffee cake I’ve ever had.
My favorite coffee shop downtown. Good coffee and kind staff.

A really cool location, we had to wait about 35-45 minutes on a Saturday which isn't bad for a city resturant.
There are vegan options, they are not good. I would recommend seeing if they will customize the regular tacos because the plant based ones were not it.
The queso and chips were to die for, I didn't get a picture because it was gone so quickly! Big serving of queso too!
My boyfriend really enjoyed the ones that he got, no complaints !
The server was very nice, the host was nice, really cool artwork and music.
Very Techno-Indy Vibe Restaurant with outstanding food. The Crown Jewel and All Nighter Tacos are worth a drive to get.
It was pretty good I had the barria quesadilla
Great food and margs!
Super cute, friendly service, amazing cookie dough!!

This place is a must visit when in Chattanooga. The edible cookie dough is fantastic. Every flavor we had was wonderful. My husband had the ice cream and he said it was very good. We enjoyed it so much, we went back the next day.
Handmade treats that are truly so delicious!!
Great little spot for a sweet treat!
Very tasty ice cream.

This place has always been my favorite, however they didn't do so swell today. We were charged 3.00 dollars extra for each meat topping. Not all of them, each one was 3.00 extra for our pizza to come out like this..pictures below. Hardly any cheese, nor hamburger meat. When I said something to the woman that cooked it, she looked at me and said "ok." Then nothing else. Didn't offer to fix it or anything. This was on 2/17/25 at 1:00pm. Kinda sad cause I love this place.
Great place to bring the family. Service is exceptional and fast. The arcade was great for the family. Love the vibe of the place. Great for all ages.

This was hard to rate because overall the food was really good. This was really good pizza! We did a half and half pizza, they got it right and it was delicious!
Huge portions!
The atmosphere… it was a Saturday and there were kids running around everywhere. It is what it is! Ours are grown…
Here’s our problems. The bartender sucked! The drinks were terrible! And the guy who originally took our order we watched collect money and then run food with the same gloves on. Overall the food was good, but people… well they will consistently disappoint even more now than before Covid!

Very crowded but with good reason! The best biscuits I've had in a while. They were operating on a limited staff so the menu was shortened which was slightly disappointing, but the things they did have available were all very tasty looking. I loved my biscuit plate. Glad to see they make their biscuits in-house from scratch! That's a rare find.

Being in the restaurant business I completely understand being understaffed and slammed with a morning rush! While we did have to wait a decent while to be helped and receive our food you could see that the staff were working hard to get orders out and that’s all I can ask for! I even witnessed attitude and frustration from customers towards the workers but the responses were nothing but apologies and accountability! Kudos to Maple Street and who they hire! We had somewhere to be so I allotted enough time incase we were stuck in a breakfast rush, which I advise for most customers!
Super friendly staff!  And the food was amazing!
My son and daughter in law recently moved to Chattanooga and I was visiting for the first time. We were there for breakfast. The chicken and waffles was the best!

Excellent breakfast spot. Seafood omelet and the Benedict are all excellent. Fresh food, friendly service, and fair prices make this a wonderful start to the morning. Solid variety of choices from traditional options to savory sandwiches or omelets to sweet choices such as French toast and pancakes. My friend had the fried green tomato and said it was awesome. Highly recommended!

Such a shame. We usually LOVE Ruby sunshine. Chose to eat breakfast here for my birthday. We walked in almost an hour after they opened and stood there for at least 5 minutes so we looked over the menu and no one ever came out to seat us or greet us. Very very disappointed.
Staff super helpful, gave great recommendations, made sure our visit was a success
Fantastic brisket and sides. Wonderful and prompt service from Megan.
Great ribs and the chicken wings are amazing

This was the first place I ate when arriving in Chattanooga, and I happily left feeling like a stuffed turkey. Lol. They know BBQ for sure. Staff was very friendly and full of good vibes and spirit. This will be a favorite of my stops in town.

ordered pulled pork, pulled chicken, ribs and brisket for take out. all phenomenal - the sauces pair perfectly with the meats. the sides ordered: the mac and cheese was great, the chili had big pieces of meat in it (stellar), and baked beans perfectly done. all in all probably one of the best bbq places I’ve had in a long time.
Burger was ok. Service was excellent. Seating out in plastic enclosed area was cold despite heaters.

We thoroughly enjoyed our dining experience at this delightful restaurant on Signal Mtn
The food was so delectable and our service could not have been better. We ordered the whipped feta hot honey appetizer, calamari, fettuccine Alfredo vegetarian and with chicken and pizza! All were delicious. We will definitely be back.
This is a really good restaurant that is continuing to improve! Highly recommend the pizza. The cinnamon rolls they serve for Sunday brunch are amazing
Pizza was cold, taste was not what I experienced in the restaurant.
Pizza is great, sometimes the Detroit style can be a little overly greasy, but other than that they have a great selection- vegetarian options, great atmosphere and service.
First time ever sing this and it was great. The guy working was great, like to cut up and very helpful. Family friendly,  nice place

As neighbors from Lexor Nail Spa, we highly recommend Craft Axe Throwing! The atmosphere is exciting and fun, making it a great place to unwind and try something different. The staff is friendly, helpful, and ensures everyone has a safe and enjoyable experience. Whether you’re a first-timer or a pro, this is the perfect spot for a unique night out. We’re lucky to have such an awesome place right next door!
Wonderfully friendly staff and a great environment. I could do without the screaming teenagers, but that just means they were having as much fun as I was!
The facility allowed us permission to throw our own axes in the building we had a great time throwing large and small ninja stars
Very relaxing place the get a beer or grab something to eat

(Late post - visited in October 2024)
We came in to get breakfast at Eggman. This is 3 companies, but in one building. It was confusing at first, but essentially you seat yourself. Eggman is served for breakfast only. And the other restaurant opens for lunch, but is the same place.

This establishment is huge. Restrooms were on the other side towards the back. They're all unisex and single stall with sinks already in the bathrooms.

Our server was extremely sweet and great at recommending items. The food was so good! We had a great dining experience. Will definitely come back to dine in when we visit Chattanooga again!

I guess you were supposed to be there all day. It took forever to be served, then just as long to get your, and it took an arm and a leg to pay. Bagel was hard, but I had no one to tell. Very disappointed.

We had dinner on the Saturday of valentines weekend and managed to get in despite the busyness! Basia was amazing and took great care of us, checking in constantly and being so attentive. Me and my friend totally lost track of time sitting there but had a great meal and amazing service. We will be back!
Such a lovely spot with ambiance galore! Baija was a phenomenal server, and really went above and beyond for us. 100000/10 will go again.
Such a great date night spot! Baisia was an amazing server as well!! She’s super attentive and genuinely cares that you have a great dining experience!

I’ve had excellent meals here, but last night was just awful. The service while very kind and friendly, was extremely slow. We had two pasta dishes, both were obviously reheated as the pasta was tough and dry in spots in the sauce was lukewarm at best. We also ordered chicken, which was very good. We ordered fries, they had to be sitting somewhere else for over 15 minutes before they made it to our table. I never send food back, but I sent back one of the pasta dishes and the fries. The fries were redone and came out piping, hot and delicious. Our server noted that they were out of the pasta dish and couldn’t provide another, needless to say I was surprised to see it still on our bill when we went to leave. I really like this place and want to support it, but it’s gonna take a while for me to want to come back after last night’s meal.

We stopped there on the way, excellent food, very friendly service and amazing attitude.
Hope to have a chance to come back for the cocktails.
Friendly, caring and delicious. Thank you 🙏🏻
I’ve tried to give this place a chance but the service here is truly terrible. I’ve been 3 different times and each time it’s the same. The food is good but not at the expense of terrible service.
I liked the ambienance and the drinks but I didn’t really like the ribs. Other than that no complaints I got the orange chicken and beef and broccoli. Just isn’t super great
