reviews.text: Super clean!! The lodge is an  amazing to stay and eat. Some of the nicest people I've ever met. The scenery is just stunning!! I will definitely be going back in the summer to see all the waterfalls
Beautiful lodge with fireplaces, comfortable seating, games for the family, and a room for kids! It was decorated for Christmas complete with a selfie stand!
We got the black bird which was great light beer and the burger… the picture speaks for itself. Delicious! The fries are great and double fried.
Such a cool vibe and great beers!

This place is my home. I've lived in Chattanooga for 8 years and have been coming here since oddstory first opened at this location in 2017. We love this place so much, my husband and I had our rehearsal dinner here -  they were so easy to work with when hosting a private event at the greenhouse. Throughout the years they have always have the loveliest staff, the best beer selections, and now an impressive selection of mixed drinks and mocktails. Their food truck has a few staple items but also a rotating menu to keep things exciting - I am never disappointed with the food here. The ambience is another reason I always find myself coming back - casual, smaller, mood lighting, games, occasional live music. Let's not forget their incredible happy hour deals. If you're looking for a chill, local spot (with no kids too) that screams "Chattanooga" this it!!

Okay, where do I start🤔Friday’s 4for$4 Flight, which allows you to sample four bartender picks from their house made brews, or “Brunch at The Greenhouse” on Sunday when the food truck is always cooking up something that will have you telling everybody about it throughout the week. Oh, the cocktails are creative and tasty also. Overall, one of the best vibes in Chattanooga and probably all of Tennessee with the best staff, hospitality and a food truck that should be nominated for The James Beard Award, if there is such a category. Anyhow, this is where I’ll be every Friday and most Sundays, redeeming my rewards, hanging out at the bar with all my friends.
Great beer, great food, and great atmosphere! Why aren't you here??

Cool place, cool vibes, food was great! We had the French toast and the salmon bagel
Both were great. We got a side of tater tots as well! It’s not the usual tater tots if you expect to get that. They’re very unique and we both loved them!!! They were seasoned very well and we thought it was a special side.
Loved this place. Went for Valentine's day, the eggs Benedict was amazing. And the service was great.
Best bagels in Chattanooga. Always good service too. 5 stars.
Quality Asian food here. Consistent service and food. Their ramen is soooo good. Best noodles in Chattanooga

Isabelle was a great server, getting us all the specials off the bat and giving a great suggestion for bao buns. The bbq platter was delicious even splitting with a friend. Outside patio can be a bit chilly but wearing another layer will keep you plenty warm, and I was impressed by the options of homemade sauces provided.

I had the pleasure of dining at Kai Bistro and was lucky enough to have Isabel as my waitress. From the moment I was seated, she provided impeccable service with a warm and welcoming attitude. She was knowledgeable about the menu, offering great recommendations and answering all my questions with enthusiasm.

I ordered the Korean BBQ platter, and Isabel made sure everything was perfect. She was attentive, refilling drinks promptly and making sure I had all the sauces and sides I needed to fully enjoy my meal.

Her friendly demeanor and professionalism truly elevated my dining experience. It’s rare to find a server who is both efficient and genuinely passionate about making customers feel valued. If you dine here, I highly recommend asking for Isabel—she’s a five-star waitress who goes above and beyond!

Would definitely return, not just for the amazing food but also for the outstanding service.
Isabel was so good to us! She was very knowledgeable of the menu and was able to guide me over the menu to find what I wanted. My food came pretty fast and it was an overall vibe.
It was my first time here and Isabel did an amazing job with recommendations and overall great service.
Great stop after walking around all morning. Nothing like a Mexican treat and drink to end the day

I drive 20 minutes to order 3 fresh coconuts #1 to go and was refused service on 10/18 because the store was about close in 5 minutes. I was asked to come back on another day. This was a very disappointing and embarrassing experience. Refusing to provide service to customers in the store because you are about to close is a bad idea for long term business success.
Insane! Best smoothie I have ever had. Triple berry yum!
This is a gem! The entire experience was wonderful from very gracious and engaging staff to a superb food! Great options for everyone and wonderful drink specials!!! We will be back!!!
Beautiful

The food was absolutely delicious—every bite was full of flavor! The restaurant was spotless, creating a cozy and inviting atmosphere. The staff was incredibly friendly, making the whole experience even better. Definitely a place worth visiting!
Great food. Beware of the breakfast burrito - it's enormous! You may want to split it :)
Great food and service! There were clean plates all around! Luke was attentive and treated us like family!
This is our boat trip lunch spot

This place has a special place in my heart. You will quickly learn what to get, and what not to get. Get the pasta or fish n chips. Do NOT get the fried mushrooms.

I like having this place as an option all the way out here, because the vibe is just so 80s with the rock wall fascia and colorful ornamental light string on the smoking deck. The local culture is great to experience, and I love walking down to the marina with my son at night. There's live music on weekends. And again, let me emphasize the pasta. I actually think about it randomly from time to time. Some of the options are beyond sub-par, so just get the pasta and be happy 😊
Great food and service
Never had anything that wasn't good here. Catfish some of the best around.
Absolutely beautiful date night spot! So pretty! Love the fireplace inside. The bar area is really nice. Definitely recommend making reservations. The mussel appetizer was so good!

The good: the Creag is a beautiful, intimate setting. The bad: the food is not great and not worth the price. We have been twice. The first time was decent at best. The second time was less than desirable. The baked potatoes our party ordered were not cooked all the way through. They were hard and wouldn’t melt butter. Some were sent back because it was so bad. The menu is very limited and very fancy. Our server the first time was incredible. Our server the second time acted like they’d rather be anywhere else… and was for much of the evening. Overall, we gave it a second chance and it was not worth it. We won’t be back.
Great food and service

This is such a beautiful resort and restaurant that our dining experience was unexpected. The food was mediocre at best.  My husband and I started with the burnt ends which were too salty, to the point it was unpleasant to eat.  We both ordered the trout for our entree which was very strong/dry.  Our friends ordered the trout “dip” which was no dip at all but rather a chunk of trout with some oil on the side.  It was served with deep fried bread which seemed an odd pairing.  The potato gnocchi that came with the trout was my favorite part of the meal.  Regarding the service, it was painfully slow…some of the slowest service I have probably ever encountered.   We had a manageable table of 6, not a huge group.  I hope this was just a bad night for the restaurant.  Ultimately we were there for the food so although it is a gorgeous restaurant/resort, the food was sub par for the cost and expectations for a fine dining restaurant of this caliber.  We won’t be back.  As an aside, we have been to Auld Alliance which was a wonderful experience both with the food and service.
Drinks and food were amazing! Best bloody Mary and Veal I have ever had. Hush puppies and salad were amazing as well! I would recommend to anyone wanting to dodge the Chattanooga traffic

The hotel looks aesthetically appealing, but there are many flaws. The beds are hard as a rock. The parking is slim after a certain time, plus there’s a nightclub that’s open until 3 that has joint parking with the hotel. The noise from the parking lot at night is terrible. Booked 2 nights and will be only staying 1.

Couldn’t ask for a better hotel for our small weekend get away! Clean and cute rooms with a modern feel! The bar is the place to be with good drinks and lively atmosphere! Lastly, staff were super friendly and inviting considering they were dealing with bar patrons at the same time! Great location… we basically walked everywhere and the valet service was super friendly and helpful!

We went away for the weekend to destress. When we got there all seemed well. We were greeted and the staff seemed friendly. However, we get up to our room and there’s barely any room to move around. There are no closets, there’s a couple of drawers under the bed But there is nowhere to set your stuff except for a small table and a chair.  The first night at around 11:30 pm one of the valets let a homeless person to use the restroom and she ended up pulling the fire alarm. So throughout the entire hotel while we are trying to rest from a long travel in, we had to listen to the fire alarm going off For 30 minutes. When it first started, I called downstairs to see if there’s anything that we should do when The answer the phone they were just unprofessional laughing and carrying on while none of us knew what we’re supposed to be doing if we should evacuate et cetera.  But then again, I don’t think it bothered all of the people that were downstairs on the first floor in the bar area playing pool, singing karaoke till after midnight and you could hear them loud and clear on the second floor where we were.  Then the hotel is obviously downtown so good luck getting any sleep with the cars that are sitting there at the stoplight right by the windows revving their engines.  The most aggravating part I think of this entire trip was the parking situation period. You can get valet parking for $16 or you can self park for $22 which makes no sense. So we chose self parking because they told us that there was parking right around the back of the hotel for guests. We were able to find a parking spot when we got there but we also arrived at around 4:30 pm. We left and had dinner and came back and there was not one single parking space open for paying hotel guests so we went into the front to ask and they said that there was overflow parking which was way out in the back lot unlit no security in downtown Chattanooga. I don’t think so. They said it was other people parking in the hotel guest parking spots that were going to other restaurants, hotels et cetera. The point is there is no parking, unless you find a place to park and Uber around town you will spend most of your time finding a place to park. So if you are wanting to distress, don’t stay here because you will get so incredibly frustrated at the fact that you just paid $22 to have secure assigned hotel guest parking and you can’t fund a spot to park!! There is a $50 deposit that you were not told about until you get there and so far. I’m on day three and still not have received my deposit back.  The door to the bathroom does not stay shut unless you lock it, and the hot water at the sink we had on full blast and it was barely warm but then the people beside us we would hear their toilet flush and then all of a sudden our water would get really hot.  Is it Clean, yes but what’s the point of staying in a clean hotel room? If you have noise the entire time you are there you can’t find a place to park and they allow anybody and everybody to come in and use the bathroom and then you end up staying awake all night because of a fire alarm and people downstairs making a bunch of noise.

This may be one of the best places I've ever stayed, it's a vibrant environment surrounding a lobby bar and lounge. Seems to attract quite a few locals as well as travelers. Highly recommend it for a very basic but somewhat small room.
used to really like it here but the new menu is not very good unfortunately. bring back the noodle basil noodle!!
Great spot for local hangout!
This is like the Cheers of Red Bank. Nothing but love.
Ehhhhh. Nothing special. Very red bank. Very low effort. Lots of tvs…
Great food and drinks!
Everything was delicious. Staff was nice and friendly. Me and my sis ate in one of the igloos, which was a neat experience.

We come here often and love the restaurants and the people in it! Lionel served us this most recent time and was kind, quick, and very accommodating. Can’t wait to come back

Also get their muffuletta, it is my favorite thing on the menu
Lionel our server was so friendly, the food and atmosphere were good too even when they were so busy.
Delicious Marriott burger with house chips. Staff is really pleasant.

Clean, calm, welcoming atmosphere. Absolutely delectable dishes with perfect flavor combinations and Top Notch ingredients. Highly professional staff, friendly and helpful service. Elevated and comfortable dining experience of five star dishes. Highly recommend.

This is upstairs at the Marriott hotel Chattanooga convention center, I stopped there for the weekend buffet and every value of the food is very fresh the service, staff, and atmosphere of customers is amazingly comfortable.

I gave this restaurant 4 stars because of the disingenuous, inhospitable, and inattentive service I received from Lady and Omkar. I felt so unwelcomed, uncomfortable, and out of place. I almost got up and left prior to our food coming to the table until MAMA TRESE CAME IN TO SAVE THE DAY!!!! We werent even her table but she could sense something was wrong. She checked on us and even checked on why our food was taking so long. Her energy, her spirit, and customer service were phenomenal!!!! She is the only reason we stayed. She is such a beautiful soul, I cannot say enough about her!!!! If she was our server from the start this would be a 5/5 review.

Service was good.

Only had the wings but they were tough and low on the flavor side. Fries were under cooked. Everything obviously came outta the freezer.

This is just another over priced Marriott bar.

They either need to lower the price or up the quality.
Best steak I’ve ever had

I dined there on 1/24/25 with a small group of people and didn’t enjoy anything about this place. We had such high hopes and wanted to experience the ambiance of dining with jazz playing in the background. Well, we were disappointed! The waitress for one was not welcoming nor was she educated on the wine selection and food. She seemed to get annoyed with us asking her about the wine. She had no clue how to explain the taste of the wine and rushed us to place our wine order. For a place that promotes upscale dining, this is not acceptable. The food on the other hand was plated very unappealing, not what is expected for that type of money. Some of the food was served to us burnt, some things were missing from the food. Just overall, it was a bad experience. I left there feeling dissatisfied.

Some friends and I had dinner on 1/24/25. From the very beginning the waitress was losing her patience; she knew nothing about the alcohol served to describe or make suggestions to us, along with the meals on the menu (and there weren't even a lot)! She brought out no condiments so everything each one of us asked for annoyed her, one time she wouldn't even acknowledge that we asked for something but brought it out anyways! The food was pricey and not good. The appetizers were burnt and when we explained to the waitress she said that they were supposed to be that way! One of the salads, a pecan salad, came with no pecans and when asked she replied that they were out of pecans, did not even think to let us know ahead of time so that we could order something else! The service was terrible and the food was bad! No wonder, even with the live jazz, they were so empty on a Friday night!

Very pricey for the quality of the food and overall experience. Waitress asked each member of our party how we wanted our meats cooked, but none were cooked accurately when our food came. We left feeling dissatisfied. Definitely not up to the standard of a Chattanooga restaurant in this price range.
Very nice staff. Good parking. Sunblaze Ipa, Belgian Dubbed very good.

What an awesome brewery! The servers and staff here were phenomenal. Everyone was extremely friendly and had lots of great suggestions about local establishments. Can’t thank all enough for the great beers and food.
We came in on a Friday night and had a blast. The bartender is friendly,attentive,and knowledgeable. 10/10 experience can’t wait to come back.
Came by for a quick visit. Loved the atmosphere and staff. The beer was great. I will definitely be coming back to check out again.
I love their brewed coffee and their specialty drinks are solid as well.   Rather inefficient service and set-up,  but the staff is pleasant.
Very good coffee and friendly service
Nice coffee shop with the usual offers (coffee and some breakfast/brunch options). Many places to sit, limited parking.
Great friendly staff and really good coffee. Coffee drinks and beans are 5/5 stars. Also, good assortment of light meals and bakery items. Plenty of indoor and outdoor seating for small groups.
Food and beer was not good but I liked the environment and the staff were nice

I cannot comment on the food since all I ordered was a cup of coffee. My review is mostly about the customer service.  I stepped to the counter after ordering and was completely ignored for least 3 minutes and when a white patron stepped in front of me the person calling out orders immediately greeted them and continued to ignore me.  I finally asked about my coffee order and I was told they were really busy. Another white lady who was behind me stated that what happened was wrong and that I was ignored so I know it wasn't just me.
Subsequently, a few moments later a completely different person called my name and sat my coffee on the pickup counter. As an HR Professional I can assure you that Training in diversity and sensitivity is truly needed at this establishment. I did not feel welcome as a customer in this establishment but did not want to ruin this trip for my kiddos. Do better Castle Cafe it is 2024!
Good
Quick
Matthew at The Bistro made our stay even more enjoyable. Super friendly guy who handled our huge group for breakfast with ease and brought on extra help for the second day.
Jordan Our cook was amazing. He had great appearance,  great attitude,  and very well knowledgeable of the menu . And instant gratification.
Very nice and clean and modern.

Coffee is delicious and it’s an added bonus that proceeds go to local missions. But do yourself a favor and try Oaks if you haven’t. The people are what make this location special. You feel seen, the atmosphere is great, and the staff are so accommodating! 10 out of 10 recommend.

It was my first time visiting Oaks Coffee House, and overall, I had a good experience. Parking was a bit of a challenge, they have a designated lot, but it was full, so I had to search for a spot. When I walked in, the place was packed, making it hard to find seating. It was a busy weekday morning around 9 a.m., so I wasn’t too surprised. Despite the crowd, the atmosphere was warm and inviting. I ordered a chai latte, and it was delicious! The barista was friendly and offered great recommendations. I’ll be back to try more from their menu but this time I'll do drive-thru.
The food was so good ate it too fast so I didn’t get a picture! The coffee is awesome ended up getting two chocolate strawberry mochas.
Great coffee, fast service. Has a drive through and great milk alternative options. Definitely recommended. Right off the interstate to boot, so that's a win.

I was really looking forward to this restaurant since I heard it was fixed up on Restaurant Impossible. However, I am sad to say the management and staff were very bad. We waited over an hour and a half to be served our meal. When our food did come out it was wrong, and the waiter seemed upset at us for her mistake. The waiter also brought me a salad that was meant for another table, and proceeded to tell the kitchen staff that I claimed the salad when she brought it out. The waiter then proceeded to charge us $7.00 for the salad we did not order. The manager did take off the salad after we told her the situation. She then proceeded to offer us a free appetizer if we came back on Thursday night. I do not believe this made up for the three hours we were there, the staff blaming me for their mistake, and them getting our order wrong. I am not giving you more business for a free appetizer. I would say the food is absolutely delicious, but if you go be prepared to wait a long time. I believe they were having a bad night and I want to give them the benefit of the doubt, but I just can’t go back after the experience we had tonight.

We visited Chattanooga this past weekend and had a wonderful meal at Blue Orleans. The food was wonderful! My husband had shrimp and grits and I had the Shrimpalaya. Both dishes were delicious! Service was great as well. Chef would walk around the dining room checking on everyone, which I felt was wonderful.

Service was excellent and the food was so tasty! Those collard greens - I could have eat 3 plates of those. Second time I have been here and not disappointed. Love the music too - nice vibe. We will definitely be back.
You won’t have a bad dish here. Food is excellent, dessert’s are fantastic and the staff is beyond amazing. Quick and very kind. Will definitely be going back!!

Seriously one of the best meals I have ever had!! The bone marrow butter is amazing!!! I highly recommend the dry aged Ribeye!  Chef Jason is a 10/10
And the Mixologist London also did not disappoint!!  He handcrafted our cocktails and made them perfect
And shout out for to Randy!!

I showed up for a work event and wasn’t able to find anyone. Juliana kindly called around to other locations and found out the event was cancelled and made me a cozy latte while I waited! So grateful for her kindness and willingness to help when I didn’t have access to my work email. Excellent service, thank you so much Juliana! :-)

The absolute best coffee in town. The quickest, most tasty brew to ever grace Chattanooga. With friendly staff, that always makes sure you're taken care of, delicious coffee and food creations, and a drive-thru line to make sure you're taken care of quickly and efficiently, you actually good never go wrong with going to Be Caffeinated. My wife and I try to support this local business as much as we can, and typically once or twice a week. I need to say it one more time for the people in the back. This is the absolute best coffee in Chattanooga. Made by Chattanoogans, for Chattanoogans.
I typically get good service here, but was bummed when I arrived at 4:30 today to see a closed sign when you clearly advertise open until 5.
Love the whole vibe

We love this place and the creative cocktails they serve! Drinks are around $16 each but so worth the price! We love coming back and checking out their new drinks. We hope they have something with ube again sometime soon!! :)
Great smoothie bowls.

This place has a wonderful ambiance with beautiful plants indoors. The service is excellent, and the juices are fantastic—fresh and flavorful. However, I wish they were served in glass bottles instead of plastic. I did a two-day cleanse and thoroughly enjoyed the taste of every juice. I also tried their wraps and crunchy salad, which are healthy, though not particularly delicious.
Love this place!

Nanobrewery in the basement. Limited selection of beers, but each one is solid. Very cool interior. Stone walls and high ceilings. Solid operation with some TVs to watch a game or foosball table or a couple couches to just relax. Limited parking. A unique brewery experience with well made beer.

Visited from out of town. The only brewery I visited and the only I will visit again from here on out in Chat.

Hard to locate, but you will be rewarded when doing so (walk down the gravel driveway, or drive it if need be).

Only meant to stop by for a minute for one, but stayed for two. This type of vibe, quality, price, service, and everything else, is exactly what all local breweries should strive to be.
Mad knight is a hidden gem! Enjoyed having a couple beers there!
Hobby brewer so don't expect a huge selection, but the owner is a nice guy who makes some good beers in a cool, old building.

A little tricky to find but worth it!(Drive [or walk] down the gravel driveway between the parking lot and the blue house.) Cool space, dog friendly if you have a friendly dog.  Never know what he’ll have on tap.  I had a light lager, imperial lager, saison, and Irish dry stout.  All very nice and his dog, inaccurately named “Caution” was an absolutely wonderful hostess to our dog “Nellie”.

The service was so bad. We have been here many times and ive never had poor service like this. We waited 20 mins before we even had water or chips added to the table. Everything was slow. We didn't get drinks until an hour in. There were other tables also complaining.
The service is 4th class and not in a good way.
Best Mexican food we have had in 4 years.
It is Highly recommended to eat and drink at Mezcla on the North Shore.   A unique atmosphere and quality ingredients are always appreciated here.

This place is awesome. Sam is the best.

love the atmosphere!! the sandwich was pretty good and the employees were chill. overall an alright experience ^^

Ordered food at 12:23pm on a Saturday and called restaurant 30 minutes later to check the status. The employee said the food was out for delivery. At 1:19pm (almost one hour since the order was put in), I received a text that the order was out for delivery and finally received it at 1:34pm, 1 hour and 11 minutes after ordering. I live a half mile from the JJ on Frazier. I like the food, but won’t be ordering food from here in the future.

OK,  this was the best Brewery in Chattanooga. Excellent beer. Golden Blackbird, Belgian Blonde, Vanta Black IPA, Dream Fever very good. Godfather Death Belgian Quad very good. And the Soul Keeper was good also. The Smash Burgers and Salad were soooo good. Stop here and relax. Great staff and patrons.
A lovely place to spend time with your friends! They have great food, nice beverages, & fabulous vibes.
Tons of seating. Inside and out. Very laid back family friendly atmosphere. Excellent beer selection. Delicious food!

Staff were completely rude, parking sucks, food there is terrible, drinks 2.5
If you're a hipster or something along those lines you'll probably love it. Other than that, I'd recommend staying away, prices aren't worth what they provide.
Totally authentic and the staff has incredible knowledge .I am european and it felt like home .The quality is outstanding

Absolutely the best ravioli I’ve ever had. The brown butter sauce with delicate lemon and tomato flavors is just absolutely stunning, and the handmade pasta is incredible. We’ve been coming here on our anniversary for fourteen years now, and the food is just as delicious as ever. I am sad that the crème brûlée isn’t available anymore, as it was stunning, but I love everything I’ve ever had from the menu. The food is northern Italian-style, and so delicious. We still make the three-hour round trip for our anniversary and it is so, so worth it. Highly recommend Boccaccia! It’s such a reasonable price for the quality of the food. Definitely make sure you get reservations ahead of time, too. It’s a small place, but I love that. Don’t miss this gem!

I was a server for 25 years so it takes a lot for me to complain.     I don’t want to go into specifics to point out any server specific.     Our meal was eternal.   Ridiculously so.
I have to say that a couple of times now I’ve seen servers spend excessive time talking to their tables while others sufffered.    Maybe work on that some.
Is there a supervisor?     The operation seemed a little rudderless.

The gem of Chattanooga! Excellent authentic Italian - both food and atmosphere. A welcome place for any big occasion and everyday treat. The caeser salad (usually quite boring at any other place) is dynamic here and the owner Luciano is a delight. The undeniable ~best~!

And a special shout out to Rebecca, our incredibly caring and charismatic waitress
OMG great brunch! You MUST try this place.

We were in town for a conference and were looking for a place to grab breakfast on the way out of town. We found this little gem and it absolutely lived up to our expectations. The food and the service were phenomenal!! Paul did an outstanding job and we will definitely come visit again when we are back in town!!
